title: lemon chicken
directions: Brown chicken in halves in hot oil for 10 to 15 minutes. Combine soup, milk, lemon juice and pepper.
Pour over chicken. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer until tender.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind and drain pears, bell peppers, red peppers, onions and dill pickles; mix.
Mix and add sugar, flour, dry mustard, salt and turmeric.
Add vinegar.
Cook 10 minutes after it comes to a boil.
Put in hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: crab bisque
directions: Sweat the mirepoix in the olive oil.
Meanwhile cook the rice in the fish stock for about 45 minutes.
To the vegetables, add the tomato paste, tarragon and pepper.
Cook the paste for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add the white wine and sherry.
Cook another 2 to 3 minutes.
Add the stock and rice and cream.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Pass through a fine sieve or food mill pressing the vegetables and rice through the sieve.
Return to the simmer.
Add crabmeat and simmer.
Adjust seasoning with salt.

title: pistachio fluff
directions: Do not drain pineapple.
Mix all together and let set until thickened.

title: paximathia(anise toast)
directions: Mix well.
Roll
into
long rolls.
Put in pan and bake until light brown,
at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Take out of oven; cut into slices, then return to oven until golden brown on both sides.

title: sweetheart coffee cake
directions: After removing from oven, drizzle with mixture of sugar, butter, vanilla and milk.
Add milk or powdered sugar to make right consistency.

title: creole beef with rice
directions: Brown meat in Crisco.
Add onion and brown slightly.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and pour into covered casserole. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in preheated oven at 375°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
Coat with flour, salt and pepper. Brown quickly in oil.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Saute over low heat until light brown.
Add Worcestershire sauce, soup and sour cream.
Bring to boil.
Dissolve beef bouillon cube in water.
Add salt, parsley and rice.
Make a well in center of meat and pour rice into well.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.

title: cream cheese drop cookies
directions: In a large bowl, with mixer at high speed, beat butter or margarine, cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Reduce speed to low; add flour, nuts, milk and vanilla.

title: ham and broccoli bake
directions: Cook frozen broccoli; drain well.
In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
In large bowl, stir together mushroom soup, celery soup, milk and cheese.
Add drained broccoli, onion, ham, uncooked rice and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Place mixture in 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake covered at 350° until rice is done, 45 to 50 minutes.
Garnish with shredded cheese.

title: jam dandy coffee cake
directions: Put all in bowl together. Beat 50 quick strokes with a fork. Pour into greased 9-inch pan. Sprinkle top with 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup nuts (chopped). Dot with jam or jelly (about 2/3 cup). Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°. Serve warm.

title: david payne's strawberry bowl(sparkling wine punch)
directions: Layer berries and sugar; let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
(Add Gran Marnier during layering if desired.)
Add wine and lemon juice; refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Add "sparkle" and serve.

title: lo-fat banana bread
directions: Beat oil and 1/3 cup sugar together.
Add banana and mix well. Sift flour and baking powder together, add to batter and beat. In separate bowl, beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add 1/3 cup sugar and beat until egg whites form soft peaks.
Fold egg whites into the batter. Pour into lightly oiled 5 x 9-inch loaf pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove from oven, allow to stand 10 minutes.
Invert bread on wire rack to cool.

title: yaki tori(grilled chicken)
directions: Cut chicken into 1/2-inch pieces and green onions into 1-inch pieces.
Place chicken and green onions on skewer.
Boil together soy sauce, rice wine, sugar and mirin for about 5 minutes.
Grill chicken and green onion, brushing with sauce twice.

title: mexican cabbage
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add cabbage and cook 5 to 10 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Spread broccoli on bottom of 9 x 12-inch dish.
Arrange chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix soup and mushrooms and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Prepare dressing according to package.
(I use broth from chicken instead of water and butter.) Spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: old-fashioned cookies
directions: Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and let stand.
Cream sugars, shortening and eggs.
In a separate bowl, mix dry ingredients. Add oats and all ingredients together and mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a sheet cake pan.
(Grease and flour optional.)

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix ingredients together until dry ingredients are wet with eggs and oil.
Beat for 4 minutes at medium speed.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for about 40 minutes. As soon as you remove cake from oven, prick with a fork and spoon icing over cake.

title: batman bars
directions: Melt in saucepan margarine and brown sugar.
Add flour, sifted with baking powder, sugar, eggs (one at a time) and nuts or raisins.
Mix; do not beat.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
When cool, cut into small squares.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pudpreu varn (pot pree a wane)(from a thailand visitor)
directions: Cut chicken from bones.
Cut into bite size pieces and set aside.
Crack chicken bones, add some skin and stew 45 to 60 minutes in 6 cups salted water.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and molasses.
Sift flour.
Add salt, soda and spices and sift again.
Add to other ingredients and mix well.
Chill and make small balls and dip in sugar.
Bake at 375°.

title: greek salad dressing
directions: Mix all together; pour over salad just before serving.

title: turkey mandarin salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine turkey, chopped onion and 2 teaspoons of salt.
Mix well.
Add grape halves, celery, mandarin oranges and cooked macaroni.
Cover and refrigerate.
Just before serving, combine mayonnaise and whipped cream.
Fold into salad along with 1/3 cup of slivered almonds.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: winter garden salad
directions: Pull apart or slice cauliflower and broccoli into bite-size florets.
Combine mayonnaise, honey, vinegar and salt; pour over vegetables.
Stir to blend thoroughly.
Cover tightly and refrigerate for at least 24 hours.
Serve garnished with minced parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: gazpacho salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine corn oil, vinegar, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss to coat well. Cover and chill.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break cauliflower into small pieces.
Chop broccoli into small pieces.
Dice onion.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Chill and serve.

title: carrots with raspberry vinegar
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Put the slices into a heavy saucepan with butter, water and salt.
Cover and let simmer over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Add raspberry vinegar and brown sugar; toss gently and let cook another 1 to 2 minutes. Garnish with chopped parsley.
Serves 4.

title: salmon roll
directions: Mix salmon, onion and sour cream and form into ball. Roll in the pecans. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: ginger chicken or "some like it hot"
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together the first three ingredients.
Place the chicken in a baking dish and spread the mixture over all of the chicken.
Bake for one hour.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: company potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skin. Cool, peel and slice in small pieces. Heat butter with soup; add onion, sour cream, cheese, salt and pepper. Mix with potatoes. Put in a greased oblong baking dish. Top with corn flakes that have been mixed with the butter. Refrigerate overnight.

title: hominy and cheese casserole
directions: Drain hominy.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter.
Add flour, onions, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Mix until smooth.
Add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add hominy to sauce.
Pour into greased, 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 40 minutes.
Can be halved.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Brown ground beef and onions. Add cabbage, tomatoes, Ro-Tel, potatoes, butter, salt and pepper. Stir and let simmer until done.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry and crumble bacon.	Mix with all other ingredients.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or longer. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: three week cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, pepper, onion and sugar.
Mix well.
Mix oil, vinegar, celery seed and salt.
Bring to a hard boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Stir until well mixed.
Let marinate in refrigerator 3 days.
Flavor improves the longer it marinates. (Will keep in refrigerator a month.)

title: hominy casserole
directions: Drain hominy.
Generously butter a 3-quart casserole dish. Layer ingredients as follows:
hominy, green chilis, salt and pepper.
Dot with sour cream and butter.
Repeat layer, ending with a layer of hominy.
Dot top with butter and pour the cream over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: greek-style macaroni bake
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Stir in next 3 ingredients; set aside.

title: mary's marinade
directions: Mix all together.
Put steak in dish, prick with fork, turn over and prick other side.
Pour mix over steak.
Cover with plastic wrap and put in refrigerator.
Turn steak three to four times during marinating.
Marinate at least four hours.

title: fannie may fudge
directions: In large pan, melt butter; add sugar and milk.
When it starts to boil, add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Keep stirring until all is melted and there are no longer white streaks.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan; chill until firm.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter.
Add onions, bell pepper and hot pepper.
Cook until well wilted.
Add tomato paste.
Cook 20 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1 cup water and add to mixture.
Cook 5 minutes. Add crawfish with 1 cup water.
Cook 25 minutes on medium heat. Serve over rice.
Be sure to cook according to specified times.

title: watermelon cookies
directions: Beat butter and shortening in a large mixing bowl on medium speed with an electric mixer.
Gradually add sugar, beating well. Stir in egg, milk and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Add a desirable amount of red food coloring to color the dough, beating until blended.
Shape dough into a ball and chill at least 3 hours.
Divide dough in half.
Store 1 portion in refrigerator. Roll remaining portion to 1/4 inch thickness on a lightly floured board.
Cut dough with a 3 inch round cookie cutter and cut the circle in half.
Place each piece on an ungreased cookie sheet and press several mini morsels in each cookie.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, but not brown.
Cool on wire rack.
Combine 10x sugar and water, mixing until smooth.
Add a small amount of green food color and dip each round edge of each cookie in the green frosting.
Place on wax paper.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg; makes a stiff dough.
Pat into bottom of pan.
Cover this with coarsely chopped nuts.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, eggs, vanilla and vinegar.
Beat well.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour.
Measure; add soda and salt; sift.
Cream fat until fluffy.
Add sugars.
Cream well.
Beat in eggs.
Add hot water; add sifted ingredients.
Add nuts, chocolate chips and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: hot swiss dip
directions: Mix the ingredients and place in a casserole sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve on crackers.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook fettucini according to directions.
Drain well and place in warm serving dish large enough for tossing.
Add butter, whipping cream, grated cheese and parsley; toss until fettucini is well coated.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, corn, milk, eggs and salt.
Set aside.
Cook ground beef and onion until well done (not brown); turn off heat. Add grated cheese and peppers.
Mix well.
Grease skillet and brown a small amount of cornmeal in bottom to prevent sticking. Pour in 1/2 of batter; spoon ground beef mixture over this.
Add balance of batter.
Cook 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: buttermilk corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix ingredients together, beating well. Place iron skillet on top of stove.
Pour in some Crisco and heat. When hot, remove from heat, then pour in cornbread batter and bake until done.

title: cheese popcorn
directions: Pop corn in hot air popper or in hot oil according to package directions.
Place popped corn in large mixing bowl.
Pour margarine over warm popcorn; toss to coat.
Add dry cheese sauce mix; toss again.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: hot tuna casserole(just loaded with healthful ingredients.)
directions: In a frypan, melt the butter.
In this frizzle the cornflake crumbs and slivered almonds until just browned.
Spoon over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Boil 1 cup of blueberries in water for 3 minutes.
Mix together sugar, cornstarch, 1/3 cup water, and salt and add to boiling blueberries.
Cook until thick, add butter.
Cool, and add 3 cups blueberries.
Pour into a 9 inch baked pie shell.
Chill, then serve with whipped cream.

title: mounds
directions: Roll ingredients in chocolate; place in refrigerator.

title: lime pear salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add pear juice and water to 2 cups.
Let Jell-O partially set.
Meanwhile, let cream cheese soften.
In blender or electric mixer, blend cheese and cream.
Add partially set Jell-O, blending well.
Fold in cut up pears and chopped nuts.
Pour into a large flat dish.
Chill overnight.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: eggless-butterless chocolate cake
directions: Blend all dry ingredients well.
Combine salad dressing and water well and add to dry ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch layer pans or tube pan.
Bake at 350° (layer:
30 minutes, tube:
40 minutes).
Test with toothpick. Ice with rich chocolate frosting.

title: molded lemon salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water, then add cold water.
When cool, add pineapple and pimento.
Then mix in whipped cream and cream cheese.
Pour into large jello mold and refrigerate until set.

title: apple butter
directions: Peel and quarter apples.
After they are peeled, put in a brass copper kettle with between 1 1/2 to 2 gallons of water.
Cook until they are tender.
You can sieve at this stage if you desire (we never do).
To this smooth sauce, add sugar.
I like to add brown sugar.
You must stir all the time with a long handle stir or it will stick and burn.
Cook until it is the thickness you like, taking out a little and testing for thickness.
We like to add flavoring last.
Have cans washed and ready and lids hot.
Can and seal.
Grimes golden apples are our favorite for our apple butter. Golden Delicious are also good.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Fold in sugar gradually and add chocolate chips and nuts.
Preheat oven to 350° and turn off after putting cookies in stove.
Leave 4 hours or overnight.
Makes 40 cookies.

title: microwaving wiener and bean pot casserole
directions: Serves 4 to 6.
Combine onion, garlic and butter in 3-quart casserole.
Microwave at High 1 to 2 minutes until onions are soft and translucent; add remaining ingredients.
Push wieners to bottom of dish so they are buried under beans.
Cover. Microwave 13 to 15 minutes until heated through, stirring, after 1/2 the time.

title: fiesta tamale casserole
directions: Layer unwrapped tamales, corn chips, chili and grated Cheddar cheese in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: zucchini "apple" pie
directions: Make pastry.
Use big zucchini, but still tender enough that you can pierce skin with fingernail.
Peel, cut in quarters, remove seeds and cut into apple slice sizes.
Toss together the zucchini, lemon juice and salt.
Mix remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Add zucchini mixture to bowl and mix well.
(It will be runny.)
Dump the filling into a 9-inch unbaked crust.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Add top crust.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
You won't believe how delicious this pie is!
Serves 8.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Combine beans, chestnuts and mushroom soup and place into buttered baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes in 325° oven.
Before serving, top with french fried onions an heat 10 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Grease a large shallow casserole.
Spread dry soup mix in bottom; add uncooked rice.
Lay desired chicken parts over top, skin side up.
Mix the soup and water together; pour over all. Cover tightly; bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Uncover the last 15 minutes to brown.
Serves 6.

title: aunt wanda's shrimp butter
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter, mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice, salt and pepper until well blended.
Add in shrimp.
Chill at least 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken fiesta
directions: Cut tortillas in strips; place on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Place chicken on top.
Mix soups, salsa, milk and onion together.
Pour on top.
Sprinkle cheese over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and sugar in a separate bowl, then mix eggs, anise oil, Crisco and margarine.
Put everything together in a bowl and mix by hand until you can form balls by hand, or spoon onto cookie sheet (floured lightly).
Bake 10 to 15 minutes, until bottom of cookie is lightly browned.

title: oreo cookie sour cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour round pan (8 x 1 1/2-inch or 9 x 1 1/2-inch).
Beat all ingredients except cookies in a medium bowl on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Coarsely chop cookies.
Stir into batter.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake springs back when touched lightly in center.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Serves 8.

title: patriotic punch
directions: Pour raspberry lemonade drink evenly into 3 ice cube trays. Freeze 3 hours or overnight.
Measure tropical punch drink mix into cap to 2 qt line.
Place in pitcher.
Add water and juice. Stir until drink mix is dissolved.
Pour into punch bowl just before serving.
Stir in club soda and blue ice cubes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir all the ingredients together, except the bacon grease.
You can use any of the following pans to
cook
this
cornbread.
Heat the 2 tablespoons bacon grease in
a 9-inch cast-iron skillet, 2 cast-iron corn stick pans with 1/2
teaspoon bacon grease in each section or 1 pie shape divided cast-iron skillet with 1/2 teaspoon bacon grease in each
section. I
prefer
the
pie shape skillet because I like a
lot
of crust.
Whichever pan you decide to use, heat the grease in
it until hot, pour batter in and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Rinse shrimp under cold water; chop.
Drain water chestnuts; chop until very fine.
Chop up green onions.
Add mayonnaise and Tabasco sauce.
Make the night before and refrigerate.
Serve as a spread on Wheat Thins.

title: stir-fry cabbage and string beans
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add chopped onions and chopped cabbage and stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add string beans and cook for additional 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cover.

title: lazy day pot roast
directions: Cover tightly and cook in oven at 275° for 8 hours.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Place cheese slices on breasts. Combine cream of chicken soup and milk and pour over breasts.
Then sprinkle stuffing mix over everything.
Drizzle melted butter over stuffing mix.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: crunchy citrus dessert
directions: In skillet, melt butter; stir in brown sugar until dissolved. Add the oat flakes and walnuts.
Stir over low heat until nuts are toasted and oat flakes are glazed.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add granulated sugar gradually and beat until stiff and glossy.
Without washing beaters, in another bowl beat the egg yolks until light and fluffy.

Beat in juice and rind of 1/2 lemon and 1 orange. Whip the cream together until blended. Sprinkle 2/3 of the oat flake mixture in a 9-inch oblong pan. Top with citrus mixture. Sprinkle with remaining oat flakes. Cover. Freeze until firm, 2 to 4 hours.
Remove from freezer 20 to 30 minutes before serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients; place in loaf pan. Cover with bacon strips if desired. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: inn maid tuna casserole
directions: In large skillet, saute onion and celery in margarine.
Stir in tuna, soup, mayo, milk, mushrooms and pimento.
Meanwhile, cook noodles according to package directions and drain.
In a 2-quart greased casserole, combine noodles and tuna mixture.
Top with bread crumbs tossed with 2 tablespoons melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly. Makes 6 servings.

title: southern lemon pie
directions: Bake pie shell; cool.
Mix 2 egg yellows into milk mixture. Squeeze juice from lemons into egg and milk mixture; stir well. Pour into cool pie shell.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top or make meringue from egg whites and form peaks.
Bake until meringue is lightly browned.
Let cool in cool, dry place.

title: make-ahead cookie mix
directions: In a very large bowl, combine butter, salt and baking powder. Using an electric mixer, blend well.
To measure flour, lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off (do not scoop or sift flour).
Add flour to butter mixture; blend until fine crumbs form, scraping bowl often.
Store in refrigerator in tightly covered container up to 4 weeks.
Makes 8 cups of mix - use for any of the variations to follow:

title: pineapple cream cheese ball
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Shape into 1 large ball or 2 small ones.
Roll into pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: swiss mushroom burgers
directions: Make into individual burgers.
Cook slow on 250° in an electric skillet until done.
Put burgers on buns; top with Swiss cheese.
Add mushrooms.
Microwave 30 seconds or until cheese has melted.

title: deer steak
directions: Cut deer steak into small pieces.
Cook in water at low temperature for 2 to 3 hours or until tender.
Add water as needed.
Add cut up green pepper during the last hour of cooking. When steak and pepper are done, add soup mix and gravy.
Dish is completed when boiling starts.

title: texas millionaire candy
directions: Mix ingredients except one cup milk, stir well and let come to a boil.
Stir well and add other cup of milk slowly (do not stop boil).
Cook until a soft ball is formed in cool water, add four cups whole pecans.
Pour into large buttered pan and place in refrigerator, overnight.
Cut into squares and dip in chocolate dip.

title: crunchy beef bake
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package. Meanwhile, brown ground beef with green pepper and garlic until beef is browned and green pepper is tender; drain. Drain noodles; combine with beef mixture, soup, tomatoes, salt and cheese. Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Uncover; top with French-fried onions and bake 5 minutes longer. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: pumpkin patch pie
directions: Place sherbet in bowl; stir until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 of the Cool Whip until well blended.
Spoon into crust.
Sprinkle with chopped Oreo cookies, pressing firmly into sherbet.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes before serving.
Garnish with finely chopped Oreo cookies and candy pumpkins, if desired.
Store leftover pie in freezer.
Makes 8 servings.
Great idea for a Halloween party!!!

title: baked mochi
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: popcorn crunch
directions: Combine popped corn and nuts, toss with butter and salt. Spread on flat pan, combine sugar, 1/2 cup butter and corn syrup in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Then boil, stirring occasionally until turns light caramel color.
Remove from heat, add vanilla. Pour over popcorn, stir to coat.
Spread out.
Break apart when cool.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 2 pounds.

title: raw broccoli salad
directions: Place olives, eggs, bacon, broccoli and cauliflower in a large salad bowl. Mix together dressing, mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese. Pour over ingredients in large bowl; mix well.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crumble Oreos to cover the bottom of rectangular dish.
Mix cream cheese with 1 cup milk, then add vanilla pudding and another cup milk.
Mix good, then add Cool Whip and mix some more.
Pour over Oreos in dish.
Crumble some more over top and refrigerate.

title: chop suey recipe
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sherry butter nut drops
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy and light.
Add salt and mix well.
Add flour alternately with the sherry, beating well. Stir in nuts.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 for 20-25 minutes.
Makes 100 cookies.

title: corn relish
directions: Cut corn from cob.
Slice onions and peppers.
Cut cabbage fine.
Add all ingredients together.
Boil together about 20 to 25 minutes.
Thicken with flour, mixing flour with a little water first.
Boil 15 minutes longer.
Seal in sterilized canning jars.

title: yeast rolls(or bread)
directions: Scald milk, then cool.
Soften yeast in warm water; let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
In a large bowl, put sugar, shortening and salt. Immediately pour scalded milk over ingredients in bowl and stir until shortening is melted.
When lukewarm, blend in 1 cup sifted flour.
Stir softened yeast and add, mixing well.
Measure 5 or 6 cups sifted flour.
Add about 1/2 the flour to the yeast mixture and beat until very smooth.
Beat in eggs; grease dough and let rise.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 2 loaves of bread or 9 x 13-inch pan rolls.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients except beaten egg.
Knead briefly and put in 2-quart greased casserole.
Cut a cross on top.
Brush with beaten egg. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Do not freeze.)

title: chocolate filled bonbons
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream Crisco, white sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and egg in large bowl at medium speed of electric mixer. Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture. Press 2 level measuring teaspoonful dough around each kiss, covering kiss completely.
Place pecan half on top of each.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 7 minutes. (Cookies will not brown.)
Gently press pecans into hot cookies. Cool on baking sheet 1 minute.
Remove to cooling racks.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Yields 3 cups dry mix. Store in airtight container.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff.
Add sugar and beat until blended.
Crumble crackers and fold into mixture.
Add pecans and vanilla and blend.
Spray pie pan with Pam and pour mixture on.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until light brown.
Cool completely.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice onions (like onion rings); saute onions in stick of butter until limp.
Place a layer of onions (about half) in casserole dish that has crumbled up Ritz crackers sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.
Repeat the layers using the balance of the onions and end with crackers.
Bake approximately 20 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix well the oil, eggs and brown sugar.
Add the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, vanilla, salt, apples and nuts. Pour into greased and floured baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fool-proof pie crust
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients. Beat remaining ingredients in separate bowl. Combine the two mixtures with a fork; then with hands. Mold dough in a bowl. Chill 15 minutes before rolling out. Will keep in refrigerator in plastic bag for 2 weeks.

title: no cook cookies
directions: Bring to a rolling boil the sugar, chocolate, cocoa, milk, oleo and vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, coconut and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: granny's no crust coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, flour, sugar, vanilla and milk.
Stir in coconut. Pour into two 9-inch pie pans.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Allow cheese and sausage to come to room temperature.
Mix together with Bisquick and work all together until completely mixed.
Roll into small balls.
Put on greased pan and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Shred cabbage in bowl.
On top of cabbage, place shredded onion and green pepper.
Sprinkle sugar on top of cabbage, onion and green pepper.
Do not stir.
Bring other ingredients to boil and pour over cabbage, etc. while hot.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or preferably overnight.
Will keep in refrigerator about a week.
Stir and remove excess oil before serving.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Slice Twinkies in half.
Layer in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Mix together all other ingredients (Cool Whip, cream cheese and milk) until smooth.
Pour on top of sliced Twinkies (center filling up).
Add choice of pie filling or serve as is.
Chill before serving.

title: hoppin john (peas and rice)
directions: Boil ham hock and fatback in 5 cups of water for 1 half hour. Add field peas
to the ham hock and fatback.
Boil peas until tender and	keep adding water until brown gravy appears. Then add rice and
let simmer with top on.
Stir with fork and let cook for 45 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: scripture cake
directions: Season to taste according to 2 Chronicles 9:9.
Spices: 1/2 teaspoon cloves, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1 teaspoon nutmeg and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Follow Solomon's prescription for making cake: Proverbs 4:23.
Bake in 2 greased bread pans (5 x 9-inch) at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: turkey creolehouston, texas
directions: Boil and bone the chicken or use leftover turkey.
Make the roux:
In a non-stick frying pan, combine the flour and oil and brown as much as you can without burning it.
Add onion and bell pepper immediately (cools it down) and cook them until soft.
Turn this mixture into a big pot and add tomatoes, okra and turkey. Add water or broth as needed.
Season with remaining ingredients to taste.

title: banana bread
directions: Start by cooking raisins slowly in small amount of water about 8 minutes. Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and bananas. Mix well and add flour, salt and nuts. Put in raisins and their juice; add soda to warm raisin water. Mix; add vanilla. Stir well and put in 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: delicious waffle mix
directions: Mix together and pour on waffle iron. THIS MIXTURE WILL NOT KEEP. However, you can cook it all and freeze. Then heat in toaster oven (not microwave). These will be as crisp as if just baked.

title: four bean baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Fry bacon crisp and break into pieces.
Mix with the rest of the ingredients in a large size crock-pot.
Cook on low setting for 6 to 8 hours.
No peeking or stirring.

title: meat balls and rice
directions: Mix rice, hamburger, egg, salt, pepper and onion.
Form ball. Fry on all sides.
Drain.
Mix mushroom soup and water.
Pour over meatballs.
Bring to boil.
Put lid on.
Turn low; stir often.

title: pennsylvania dutch coleslaw
directions: Shred
the
cabbage and onion into a large mixing bowl, then stir
in the sugar.
Set this mixture aside while making the dressing.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in bowl.
Blend next 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Pour over dry ingredients, stirring until marshmallows melt.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done.
Frost with Coca-Cola Frosting.

title: asparagus caesar
directions: Cook asparagus in a small amount of water 6-8 minutes or until crisp tender; drain.
Place asparagus in a 12x8x2 baking dish.
Combine butter and lemon juice; pour over asparagus. Sprinkle cheese and paprika over asparagus.
Place under broiler until browned.
Garnish with lemon, if desired.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Sift together first 7 ingredients.
Cream sugar and butter. Add dry ingredients alternately with tomato soup, add raisins.
Use chopped nuts to top frosting bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour in greased and floured loaf pan.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: In the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan, place the chicken pieces, then layer evenly on top the Swiss cheese, dried bread crumbs from the stuffing mix, then the seasoning packet from the stuffing mix. In a small bowl stir together the can of soup and 1 soup can of water.
Pour this mixture over the top to moisten all the bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Allow to stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving, covered, so chicken will reabsorb the juices.

title: boxing-day pies(pork pies)
directions: Place all ingredients in a large saucepan (kettle).
Cover with boiling water, paddling it thoroughly; simmer slowly about 1 hour, stirring frequently so that meat does not solidfy.
Fill pie; pour out excess moisture, but do not remove all.
Bake at 375° about 1 hour.
Makes 4 pies.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook corn syrup, sugar and water to 238°.
Add butter and peanuts.
Cook to 300° or hard crack stage.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and soda.
Stir until foamy and pour quickly onto a buttered cookie sheet.
Break when cool.

title: fresh corn saute
directions: Cut corn from cob.
Heat butter in large skillet.
Add corn, onion, green pepper and oregano.
Cover and cook 6 to 7 minutes until tender.
Stir and shake occasionally.
Add salt, sour cream and tomatoes and cook only until tomatoes are hot, not mushy!

title: easy pot roast
directions: Place roast in casserole dish. Fill with water to 1-inch from top of dish. Add Worcestershire sauce and lots of salt and pepper. Cut up onion and place in water. Cook at 325° for 5 hours. Add diced carrots and potatoes; cook 1 hour longer and serve.

title: oysters pierre
directions: Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter and set aside.
In heavy skillet or pan, melt 4 tablespoons butter; add flour and cook on low heat, stirring constantly until light brown.
Add garlic, green onions, parsley and Kitchen Bouquet and cook 5 minutes.
Add cayenne and salt; blend in sherry.
Add oysters and mushrooms and simmer 5 minutes.

title: mrs. bowie's bean and corn casserole
directions: Mix beans and corn in casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over beans and corn.
Mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add topping.
Bake 10 more minutes.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of mushroom

title: miniature pizzas
directions: Put slices of party rye bread on cookie sheet.
Place other ingredients on in order.
When ready to serve, toast under broiler until cheese is melted and beginning to brown.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Bake pie crust.
In pan stir cornstarch, salt and 1 cup sugar. Stir in 1 1/2 cups water, lemon peel and juice; cook until lemon mixture is thick and boils, stirring constantly.
In bowl, beat yolks; stir in small amount of hot mixture.
Slowly pour yolk mixture back into lemon mixture, stirring rapidly to prevent lumping.
Return to heat; cook, stirring constantly until lemon filling is thickened; do not boil.
Stir in butter; pour into pie crust.
Cool 10 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400°.
In small bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Gradually sprinkle in 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread meringue over pie.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden.

title: cooked play dough
directions: Combine flour, salt and cream of tartar in a large saucepan. Gradually stir in a cup of water with food coloring mixed in it. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until a ball forms. Remove from the heat and knead until smooth.
Store in an airtight container.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix in order.
Bake at 350° in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in preheated oven for 1/2 hour or until done.

title: linguine with shrimp
directions: Heat a large pot of water.
When it comes to a boil, add the linguine.

title: kentucky colonels
directions: Combine butter, condensed milk and bourbon in a large mixing bowl; add sugar and knead until mixture is well blended and does not stick to hands.
Knead in chopped pecans.
Shape in 1-inch balls.

Combine chocolate morsels and paraffin in top of a double boiler; place over hot water, stirring until chocolate is melted. Using a toothpick, dip each ball of candy into chocolate mixture. Place on waxed paper.
Remove toothpick and gently press a pecan half on each.
Yield:
About 6 dozen.

title: beef teriyaki
directions: Combine soy sauce, sake or sherry, sugar, mustard and garlic. Add meat to marinade and let stand at least 15 minutes at room temperature.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and smooth.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and soda together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Then add buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients alternately, beating after each addition.
Fold in bananas and pecans.
Cook in layers at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: dilled vegetable sticks
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add beans, carrots and celery.
Return mixture to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Place vegetables in a shallow container; pour vinegar mixture over vegetables.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: ugly cake(triple tasty fudge bars)
directions: Combine
dry cake mix, 1/2 cup prepared frosting, water and egg.
Stir	by
hand until cake mix is moistened.
Mixture will be stiff.
Pat
into	13 x 9-inch pan, greased on bottom only.
Beat sour
cream into remaining frosting.
Spread over base and sprinkle
with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Top
will
be
puffy.
Chocolate chips do not melt. Cool and cut into bars.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler and let cool, then stir in slightly beaten egg yolks.
Whip cream and stir in chocolate chips.
Beat egg whites until stiff and stir in sugar.
Then fold into the chocolate mixture.
Break angel food cake into small pieces and put a layer in large buttered dish, then a layer of chocolate mixture, then another layer of angel food bits and then a layer of chocolate mixture.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Will make a serving for 12 or 14.

title: apple cabbage slaw
directions: In a bowl toss apple with lemon juice.	Add remaining ingredients and toss to coat.
Refrigerate any leftovers.
Yield 4 servings.

title: fiesta pasta
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions and set aside. In 12-inch skillet, heat oil over medium heat and saute zucchini, onion, peppers and garlic for 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes, oregano and salt and heat to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring frequently until the mixture thickens.
Serve tossed with pasta.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 side dish servings.
For less spice, use hot cherry peppers.

title: cheap cupcakes
directions: Cream the butter; add the sugar gradually, then the egg and beat well.
Add the water and let this stand while the flour and baking powder are sifted three times.
Beat all together thoroughly and bake in a moderate oven.
This may be used as a loaf or as a layer cake with any preferred filling.

title: mayonnaise chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at
350° until done (30 to 35 minutes).
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: norwegian stuffing
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Stuff turkey firmly.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Put turkey in oven, then get out of kitchen because you are going to blow the butt off your turkey!

title: lizzie's vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients to make a dip for carrots, celery, salads, etc.
Mix to taste.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook and stir onion in butter.
Stir in flour until well blended.
Add salt, pepper, broth and milk; mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Last, stir in broccoli.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Mix all together except 1 cup of cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle them over top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: marzietti
directions: Chop onion; fry with ground beef until brown.
Cook noodles and celery together in salted water; drain.
Drain peas, combine with the rest of ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Put in baking dish.
Cover top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add milk and sugar.
Bring to boil for 1 minute; remove from heat.
Stir peanut butter, vanilla and cocoa in, then fold in oats.
Spoon out on wax paper.

title: strawberry rhubarb cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam. Place rhubarb and strawberries in bottom of pan.
Combine flour, sugar, milk and almond extract.
The dough will be lumpy.
Pour over the fruit.
Do not stir.
Pour melted margarine over the dough.
Use a toothpick to swirl into the dough.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Great with ice cream.

title: diet yogurt pie
directions: Whip yogurt and Cool Whip together and add fresh fruit, if desired.
Add to graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.
Yield: 1 pie.
One medium-size piece has 72 calories.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar, cocoa and milk; bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Remove from
heat; add oats, peanut butter and vanilla. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Cool.
Can leave out peanut butter, if desired.

title: fullabull's sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onions; prepare noodles.
Mix sausage mixture and noodles in casserole dish.
Mix together the 2 cans of soup and Pet milk.
Pour over sausage and noodle mixture; stir a bit.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Heat in oven until hot and bubbly.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in an air tight container.

title: saute mushrooms
directions: Heat saute pan; add olive oil along with garlic and thinly diced onion.
Saute until onion is transparent.
Add mushrooms; saute for 1 to 2 minutes, then season with salt to taste.
Cover and continue cooking 3 to 5 minutes.
Add wine and lemon juice; cover and simmer for 1 minute.
Serve and enjoy.

title: miracle coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Pour into pie dish.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Use a 9 1/2 x 2-inch scalloped foil pan or a 9 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and mashed bananas.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Pour into loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pickled beets
directions: Wash beets.
Leave 1 inch of stem and top root to prevent bleeding.
Cover with boiling water and cook until tender. Combine all ingredients, except beets; simmer 15 minutes.
Pack beets into jars, leaving 1/2 inch head space.
Remove cinnamon from liquid.
Pour boiling hot liquid over beets.
Adjust lids. Process 30 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: candied dill pickles
directions: Slice pickles and cover with ice; when it melts (about 5 hours), drain.
Mix sugar, vinegar and pickling spices.
Pour over pickles.
Let stand for 3 days, stirring every day.
(Do not cover.)
Put in jars on the third day.

title: grandchildren's favorite rice and chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and broccoli in butter until tender; add to rice. Also add celery and mushroom soups, mushrooms and chicken.
(Cut chicken into bite size.)
Blend all the above and add Cheez Whiz. Mix well.
Cover with foil and bake at 250° (stir often to spread cheese) until hot.
Can be mixed day before.
Ready for oven.

title: coffee squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Place in cake pan.
Top with morsels and walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: best ever cake
directions: Prepare cake by package directions and spoon into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°.
Remove and punch holes all over the surface of the cake with toothpick.

title: chicken delicious
directions: Place spaghetti and chicken in baking dish.
Combine milk, salt, pepper, soup and butter.
Mix together well.
Pour over spaghetti.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pea pickin' cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, mandarin oranges and Crisco oil together. Bake in layer pans.
Let cool thoroughly.
Take Dream Whip or Cool Whip.
Add vanilla pudding mix.
Stir in crushed pineapple. Spread on cake.
Place in refrigerator for a while before cutting. This is a cool, light dessert that is delicious.

title: oatmeal gems
directions: Beat butter/margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add combined flour, baking soda and cinnamon. Mix well.
Stir in oats.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Indent center.
Fill each with 1/4 teaspoon preserves.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 2 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in a covered jar in the refrigerator.
Will keep 2 or 3 weeks.

title: out of sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: white bread
directions: In a large bowl, add 1/2 cup of water, yeast and sugar.
Set for 5 minutes.
Add warm milk and lukewarm shortening.
Add eggs, flour and salt.
Make a stiff dough.
Let rise for 1 1/2 hours. Punch down and form into 4 loaves.
Let rise for 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: elephant ears
directions: Stir flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder, and salt in a medium bowl.
Stir in milk and 3 tablespoons melted oleo until dough forms.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead 10 times.
Pat with hands into a 9 x 5-inch rectangle.
Using a pastry brush, brush rest of oleo on top.
Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons sugar that was mixed with the cinnamon.
Roll dough up tightly.
Pinch edges to seal.
Cut into 4 equal parts.
Place cut sides on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes, until golden brown.

title: pink fluff
directions: Put egg whites and strawberries in blender; blend thoroughly. Pour in sherbet dishes and place in freezer until ready to serve. Makes 4 to 5 servings.
Some good.
Try it.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wild rice garden casserole
directions: Boil carrots, zucchini and broccoli, 5 to 7 minutes or until desired tenderness.
Drain.

title: refrigerator nut wafers
directions: Blend dry cake mix, water, vanilla extract and egg. Work in nuts with your hands. Shape into 2 inch rolls. Wrap in wax paper and chill thoroughly in refrigerator or freezer.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Combine beans and mushroom soup in casserole, using bean juice for liquid.
Sprinkle onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with vegetables.

title: rosy pear compote
directions: In saucepan, combine first 5 ingredients.
Bring to boiling. Place pears and orange slices in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour cranberry mixture over fruit.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until pears are tender.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together and heat.
Will do about 4 chickens.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Combine all, blending well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Freeze.
Take out of freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: ranch dressing
directions: Beat together.
Chill at least 12 hours.
Makes 2 cups.
Keeps 2 weeks in the refrigerator.
Contains 20 calories per tablespoon.

title: spicy chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in casserole in 1 layer.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Marinate in refrigerator for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: nacho dip
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Mix 1/4 cup of soup with other ingredients.
Add a little water, if needed.
Form balls and put into peppers.
Additional balls can be put between peppers.
Pour remaining soup and 1 can of water over peppers.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to barely boiling.
Cover and cook 1 hour.

title: pear salad
directions: To a cup of heated pear syrup, add lime jello.
When dissolved, add in cream cheese, mashing and dissolving as much as possible.
Then add the mayonnaise and mashed pears.
When gelatin mixture is slightly cooled, add Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: spinach and chicken mostaccioli casserole(low-fat)
directions: Cook mostaccioli; drain.
Place spinach on paper towel; squeeze until barely moist.
Coat large nonstick skillet with spray; add oil.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add onion and garlic; saute until tender.
Add chicken; cook until chicken loses its pink color, stirring constantly.
Stir in tomatoes and next 5 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine pasta, spinach, chicken mixture and 1/4 cup cheese in bowl.
Stir well.
Spoon into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish coated with spray.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: banana whip
directions: Combine marshmallows and orange juice.
Let stand until marshmallows are soft.
Add apple, banana and lemon juice.
Beat until light.
Carefully fold in sweetened whipped cream.
Pile lightly in stemmed glasses.
Garnish with candied cherries. Yields 6 servings.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out water.
Mix soup mix, sour cream, mayonnaise, chopped onion and spinach.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Delicious with fresh vegetables.

title: zucchini vermicelli toss
directions: Cook the vermicelli.
When almost cooked, add zucchini until it's all cooked.
Drain them.
Heat the oil in skillet.
Add garlic.
Saute until golden.
Add the rest of garlic, oil, Parmesan cheese, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hermit oatmeal cookies
directions: On a sheet of wax paper, stir together flour, baking soda and spices.
In a large bowl, cream the butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Beat in until blended the eggs, milk and vanilla. Add the flour mixture and mix well. Stir in the oats, raisins and walnuts. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls, well apart, onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. With a wide spatula, remove to wire racks to cool.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Drain and remove center bone from salmon.
Break up thoroughly. Mix in onion, toasted crumbs, seasonings to taste, egg and honey Dijon.
Form small to medium patties.
Coat with corn meal. Skillet brown patties in vegetable oil.
Makes about 8 medium cakes.
Great with pasta.

title: auntie judy's famous mexican dip
directions: Spread Bean Dip in bottom of 9x12 pan, Mix mayo, sour cream and taco mix and pour evenly over bean dip.
Add Shredded lettuce on top of sour cream mixture, sprinkle chopped tomato, then add cheese. Add sliced olives.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine egg yolks, salt and milk; mix well.
Place over low heat, stirring constantly, until warm.
Combine sugar and flour, mixing well.
Gradually add to milk mixture, stirring constantly. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and coconut.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Mix cake mix with milk and shortening.
Put 1/2 of mixture in a 15 x 10 x 3/4-inch cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.

title: peach cake
directions: Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes in layers or 1 hour in tube pan.

title: chocolate berry wedges
directions: Grease 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a small mixing bowl, stir together flour, cornstarch and salt.
Set aside.
Beat butter, sugar and brown sugar until creamy.
Stir in eggs, one at a time. Stir in chocolate and vanilla.
Blend with flour mixture.
Fold in 1/2 cup preserves and pour mixture into pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brownies spring back when lightly touched in center.
Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Spread with 1/3 cup of preserves.
Pour chocolate glaze over top.
Cool completely before cutting into wedges.
Top with raspberries.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet and then drain. Combine all ingredients in slow cooker. Cover and cook on low for 4 hours or until ingredients are heated through. Serve with cheese, sour cream and tortilla chips. Great for a crowd.

title: simple punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a container.
Fill remainder of container with water.
Add food coloring, if desired.

title: school house rolls
directions: Mix yeast with 1/2 cup warm water; set aside. Combine dry milk and add 1 1/2 cups warm water, sugar and shortening. Stir well. Add yeast and stir. Add enough flour to make like paste. Let rise 45 minutes. Then add salt and enough flour to make dough. Roll out, cut and let rise 1 hour or more. Bake at 425° until brown. Brush with butter.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In 8 or 9-inch cake pan, combine pecans with the melted butter.
Toast in oven for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add salt, soy sauce and hot pepper sauce; toss. Makes 2 cups.

title: cream cheese in round bread
directions: Cut off top of bread loaf and scoop out inside, leaving about 3/4-inch thick shell.
Cube removed bread; set aside.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Fill shell.
Put top on and wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Use cubes to dip; also good with crackers.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt butter or margarine in saucepan.
Blend in flour to make a smooth paste.
Add milk and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly over medium heat, until thick and smooth.

title: colored punch
directions: Mix all together except 7-Up.
Just before serving, add 7-Up. Good to use for weddings and showers because of Kool-Aid.
Goes with whatever color you need.

title: glazed pecans(with dr.  pepper)
directions: Cook pecans, butter, and Dr. Pepper in saucepan, stirring frequently until all liquid is evaporated.
Place on baking sheet; sprinkle lightly with curry powder.
Roast at 300 degrees about 30 minutes or until crisp.

title: microwave shrimp scampi
directions: If desired, the shrimp may be butterflied.
In a shallow 2-quart heat resistant, nonmetallic baking dish, place butter, parsley flakes, lemon juice, garlic and salt to taste.
Heat, uncovered, on full power for 2 minutes.
Add shrimp; stir to coat well.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Heat, uncovered, on full power for 6 minutes.
Stir shrimp occasionally.
Cook just until shrimp are pink and tender.

title: knox blox
directions: Mix together, pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.

title: peach preserves
directions: Cook peaches and sugar 15 to 20 minutes, stirring often.
For thicker preserves cook until desired thickness.
Remove from heat; add spices.
You may use more or less spices.
Overripe peaches work best.

title: beef stew with dumpling
directions: Add salt and pepper to 1 cup flour.
Toss meat until coated. Heat oil in large Dutch oven.
Add meat and brown.
Pour onion on meat and saute 5 minutes.
Cover with water and add salt, pepper and bouillon.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 2 1/2 hours until tender. Add carrots.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add potatoes; cook until tender. Mix 6 cups Bisquick with milk as directed.
Drop on simmering stew by spoonful.
Cook 20 minutes, uncovered, then 15 minutes, covered, until dumplings are set and done.

title: pasta e fagioli(italian bean soup)
directions: Heat water and beans to boiling in Dutch oven; boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover; let stand 1 hour.
Add onion, tomato sauce, celery, garlic, meat, bouillon and salt to beans. Cover and simmer until beans are tender, about 2 hours (do not boil).
Stir pasta into soup.
Simmer until pasta is tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese when serving.
Good with fresh Italian bread.
Serves 5.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2-quart casserole and bake at 300° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: preacher's baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients into a large heaping bowl!
Put into pan and cook for a while.
Eat!
Or, drain beans and pineapple and mix together.
Add brown sugar, onion and salt and mix together.
Add liquid smoke, molasses, mustard and barbecue sauce; mix together. Saute sausage and drain.
Mix sausage and other ingredients. Place mix into baking pan and bake at 425° for at least 1 hour.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Add steamed broccoli to rice.
Add soup to Cheez Whiz and mix; heat until bubbly. Layer mixture of broccoli and rice.
Top with soup and cheese mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage, egg and cheese casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain. Layer sausage, bread cubes and cheese. Mix eggs, milk and mustard.
Pour over sausage mixture. Cover with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Serves 6.

title: tomato-yogurt soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except parsley.
Chill.
Serve chilled in a bowl sitting in a larger bowl of ice cubes.
Garnish.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish apples.
Combine white sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Mix ingredients and spread over apples. Mix flour, oats, brown sugar, baking powder and melted butter. Combine and sprinkle over apple mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°. Top with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar. Add egg and vanilla. Work in 2 1/2 cups flour. Pinch off dough and make small balls. Dough will be sticky, so roll it in 1/2 cup flour. Mash flat on cookie sheet and bake at 300° until golden brown.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Melt chocolate chips, vanilla, milk and margarine in microwave until melted.
Put nuts and marshmallows in large pan.
Pour mixture over this and mix well.

title: peanut butter jumbos
directions: Beat together margarine, peanut butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs.
Add flour and soda.
Mix well.
Stir in candies.
Drop dough onto greased cookie sheet.
Press 3 to 4 additional candies into each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 13 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix and set in refrigerator.

title: harvest fruit bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine first four ingredients in medium bowl; set aside, stirring occasionally.
In large bowl beat together margarine and sugar.
Add combined flour, oats, and 1/2 teaspoon apple pie spice.
Beat until crumbly.
Reserve 3/4 cup oat mixture for topping.
Press remaining oat mixture onto bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Spread fruit evenly over crust to within 1/4 inch of edge.
Combine nuts and reserved oat mixture; sprinkle evenly over fruit.
Pat down lightly.
Bake 16 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely; cut into bars. Store loosely covered.
Yields 32 bars.

title: low calorie eggnog
directions: Combine egg yolks and milk in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat until mixture coats a metal spoon.
Let cool.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Add the egg custard mixture, vanilla flavoring and Equal sweetener. Mix lightly. Cover and chill. Pour into serving cups and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes 8 1/2 cups.

title: miracle cobbler--peach
directions: Melt margarine and grease the sides of 9 x 9 baking dish. lay fruit on melted margarine.
Pour batter over fruit and bake for 20-45 minutes at 375°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Thaw strawberries. Add pie filling. Add bananas before serving.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Boil shrimp with the seafood seasoning to taste for 12 minutes.
Let soak in same water for 1/2 hour.
Peel shrimp.

title: turnips
directions: Place meat in enough water to cover and simmer until tender. Fresh meat will need 1 1/2 teaspoons salt.
Wash turnip leaves several times; remove stems and cook in meat stock for 1 hour or until tender.
Turnip roots may be added during last 30 minutes of cooking. Just peel and slice.

title: easy fudge
directions: Stir together in a heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan, sugar, margarine and milk.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly. Boil for five minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add other remaining ingredients; mix until well blended.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature. Cut into squares.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini slices in water.
Use part of water in casserole.
Break up bread.
Mix together and bake at 350° until done.
Add more grated cheese 3/4 cup and let melt.

title: my mom's pizza
directions: Buy pizza crust at the Farmer's Market, Bun Basket or make your own.

title: peanut brittle(microwave cooking)
directions: Place sugar, corn syrup, water, salt and peanuts in dish. Cook on
High for 13 to 15 minutes or until syrup separates into threads.
This is hard crack stage (300°) on candy thermometer. Check temperature with thermometer several times during the last few minutes. (Don't leave thermometer in while cooking.)
Stir in butter, baking soda and vanilla just until light and bubbly.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool, then break into pieces.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour over 2 packages of oyster crackers.

title: del miller's double good berry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in pan.
Add water and 2 cups berries.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and clear.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and lemon juice. Cool.
Mix in 2 cups uncooked berries.
Pout into 9-inch baked shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; melt butter, cube bread and saute in butter.
Grease 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Divide vegetables and bread mixture.
Put in layer of vegetables, then layer of bread. Top with 1/2 of cheese and repeat.
Mix 2 soups and pour over. Cover and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Add hot water, flour, soda and vanilla.
Mix M&M's with a spoon.
Drop onto a greased cookie sheet and bake in a 350° to 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: stuffed round steak
directions: Spread on 1 1/2 pounds beef round steak.
(First, bone steak and pound flour into both sides; brush off excess flour.)
Roll up and tie securely.
Brown on all sides in a little hot fat in large heavy utensil.
Add 1/2 cup hot water.
Cover; cook 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.
Uncover and cook 1/2 hour longer.
Add thickening to juices in utensil for gravy.

title: country pecan muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center of mixture.
Combine milk, butter, eggs and vanilla; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, then at 325° for 1/2 hour.
Place a pan of water in the oven. Makes one loaf.

title: rhubarb strawberry pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar and flour.
Add rhubarb and strawberries, tossing lightly.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Place mixture into pie crust, mounding in center.
Dot with butter. Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until filling bubbles.

title: sausage balls
directions: Roll into balls and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: hamburger upside-down casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as package label directs until just tender. Drain.

title: addies fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cream, butter and cocoa in saucepan.
Stir until blended.
Bring to full boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Pour into large bowl.
Combine peanut butter and marshmallow.
Whip at high speed with electric mixer until creamy smooth.
Pour in buttered pan.

title: ron's barbecue beans
directions: First brown hamburger meat in skillet.
Then add ketchup, mustard, Showboat beans, onion bits barbecue sauce and Sassy Jones barbecue sauce.
Let simmer, then add Tabasco sauce, brown sugar and honey.
Sprinkle with salt and black pepper.
Cook until done.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice. Stir in tuna fish.
Serve with raw vegetables as a dip or spread on fresh bagels for a tasty snack.

title: tennessee volunteer salad
directions: Pour dry jello over drained fruit.
Mix well and add remaining ingredients.
Chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: seafood sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Reserve 1/2 of the red pepper for garnish.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: hogue style tacos
directions: Brown meat and onion in medium saucepan.
Remove from heat. Blend beans in blender until smooth.
Add tomato sauce and hot sauce to hamburger.
Heat and serve over crushed chips.
Add cheese, salad and sour cream (if desired).

title: no bake cookies
directions: In large saucepan mix together sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add milk and butter and cook over medium-high heat until mixture comes to a rolling boil stirring constantly.
Continue cooking and stirring for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and then quick oats.
Drop only wax paper or tin foil by teaspoon.

title: cucumbers with spicy dressing
directions: Peel cucumbers and cut them in half lengthwise into halves. With a small spoon, scrape the seeds out of each half, leaving hollow, boat-like shells.
Cut the cucumbers crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.

title: pecan cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Put pecans in bottom of pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour in pan.
Bake at 350° until done, about 1 hour.

title: apple pie
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt using a fork or pastry cutter until it resembles small peas. Add cold water just until a ball forms. Let dough rest while you make filling.

title: american lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Place in a large baking dish.

title: cream wafers
directions: Mix butter, cream and flour thoroughly.
Chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board. Cut into 1 1/2-inch round cookies.
Coat both sides of cookie with sugar (granulated).
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Prick cookie in 4 places with fork.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes until slightly puffy.

title: old-fashioned sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Stir twice while baking.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients well together.
Store in airtight container. Use 3 teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: teriyaki pot roast
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and curry powder.
Dredge meat in seasoned flour.
Brown in shortening.
Pour off drippings.
Add water, honey, soy sauce and ginger.
Cover tightly and cook slowly for 3 to 3 1/2 hours at 325° or until meat is tender.
Add 3/4 cup water to cooking liquid; add 1/4 cup flour to make gravy.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well. Add oil, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
This mixture will be very stiff.
Add pineapple, carrots and pecans.
Pour in a greased loaf or tube cake pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until good and brown.

title: steamboat chicken
directions: Brown chicken in frying pan coated with cooking spray.
Put chicken in square glass pan sprayed with cooking spray and top with soup.
Top with Italian seasoning and seasoned salt (Lawry's or any extra Market Day seasoned salt that is lying around).
Count to ten when sprinkling (saying "Steamboat" as opposed to "All-i-ga-tor"). Top with shredded Colby Jack cheese or whatever cheese is in cheese drawer.
Use 1/4 to 1/2 of a package or whatever amount is leftover in the package.
Top one more time with Italian seasoning and/or whatever salt is available.
Count to whatever you wish.
Cover dish with aluminum foil.
Brown in oven at 350° for at least 1/2 hour.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine all ingredients; mix well. Pour into pastry shell and bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake 35 to 40 minutes longer or until knife inserted 1 inch comes out clean.
Cool; garnish.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: Beat condensed milk and peanut butter into cream cheese.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping and turn into pie shell.
Drizzle 2 teaspoons of chocolate syrup on top and swirl in.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: old timey chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar,
cocoa,
Karo
and milk in saucepan and cook until you get
a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and
add
margarine and vanilla.
Beat awhile, then add nuts
and pour
into platter greased with margarine.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: egg, sausage, cheese souffle
directions: Fry onion, pepper and garlic.
Remove sausage from skin and fry.
Drain well.
Beat eggs and Ricotta.
Add baking powder and flour.
Mix add sausage, cheese, onion, pepper and garlic mixture. Butter and flour a souffle type dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour until golden brown.
(Test center after the hour to see if set. Cook until center is set.) I sprayed dish with Pam.
Run a knife around to loosen from pan.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Combine milk, chocolate chips and margarine in microwave until melted.
Be careful not to overcook.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well with spoon.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Cookies will be soft and chewy like a brownie.

title: milk shake(lo-cal)
directions: Put in blender.
Chop 8 to 12 ice cubes or until as thick as you want.
Can also use a fruit, such as 1/2 banana, 1/2 cup pineapple or 1/2 cup peaches.
Blend in with the ice.
Makes 2 big glasses.

title: crock-pot cheese pie
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed on package. Grease crock-pot with cooking oil. Mix eggs, milk and melted margarine together. Fold in cheese. Drain cooked macaroni and add to other ingredients. Salt and pepper to taste. Pour into crock-pot and cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream sugar, butter and peanut butter. Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla. Sift together flour, salt and soda. Stir into egg mixture (may have to use hands). Shape into balls. Roll in additional granulated sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Immediately put chocolate candy kisses into each.

title: edible play dough
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Mix in powdered sugar.
Blend until smooth.
Food coloring may be added.
(Kids have fun.)

title: millionaire candy
directions: In double boiler, melt caramels with 2 tablespoons of water. When melted, add pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on buttered cookie sheet.
Place in refrigerator to cool.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until mixed thoroughly.
Add buttermilk and dissolved yeast.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Cover bowl and put in refrigerator until ready to use as needed.
Roll out on floured board to 1/2-inch thickness and cut.
Bake at 400° in a shallow pan until brown or about 12 minutes.
Dough will keep in refrigerator for about 2 weeks.

title: yorkshire pudding(this recipe is best with mutton)
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add 1/2 of milk and flour.
Mix.
Add rest of milk.
This will be quite runny.
Pour into greased dripper that you have your roast in.
Remove most of the juice from roast.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add oil and beaten eggs; mix well. Gradually add carrots and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken and rice dressing
directions: Combine margarine and lemon juice.
Brush chicken with mixture and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Combine rice, chicken broth and water in saucepan; bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Cook sausage, onion and celery until sausage is done.
Combine rice and sausage.
Stir well. Spoon mixture around chicken and bake for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: amy's chicken-rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice as directed.
In large (3-quart) casserole, layer as listed through pimentos.
(Amy is from New Mexico and adds 1 can green chili peppers, too.)
May be made ahead this far (up to one day).

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in small amount of oil and place in baking dish.
Put a spoonful of Stove Top stuffing (prepared according to directions on box) on top of each pork chop.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: orange sherbet punch
directions: Soften sherbet and mix all ingredients together.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: quick and easy mocha fudge pie
directions: Combine hot water and 2 teaspoons coffee granules in a medium bowl; stir well.
Add brownie mix, 1 teaspoon vanilla and egg whites; stir until well blended.
Pour mixture into a 9-inch pie plate coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 22 minutes.
Let crust cool completely.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in tea; add the pineapple juice to make 2 cups.
Stir in fruit and water chestnuts.
Place in 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Top with Cool Whip.
Serves 6.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, Parmesan, chopped garlic, cut up artichokes and Worcestershire.

title: fried asparagus in beer batter
directions: Mix flour and seasonings together. Add beer to dry ingredients, mixing slowly until thick enough to stick to asparagus. Cut asparagus into 2-inch pieces. Heat olive oil. Deep-fry the coated asparagus in 2-inches of oil until golden brown, turning once.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald milk; add 1
cube
of
butter
or
margarine.
In another bowl, mix yeast,
water and 1 teaspoon sugar to proof. Beat the eggs and add
to
milk
mixture
when
it is lukewarm along with yeast mixture,
salt
and 1/4 cup sugar.
Stir well and add flour until it	is mixed well.	Should be thick, moist dough. Cover tightly and put in refrigerator overnight.

title: fiesta bacon dip
directions: Beat together cream cheese, mayonnaise and taco mix until smooth.
Spoon mixture on a 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with layers of lettuce, bacon, tomatoes, cheese and olive slices, mounding towards center.
To serve, allow guests to scoop dip with corn chips.

title: mushrooms stuffed with crab meat
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Put a little salt and cook in oven 15 minutes.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
After the mushroom caps are cooked, cool, then stuff mixture.
Serve as appetizers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until almost done.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together into a large casserole dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: parmesan potato sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Coat a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Mix well and set aside.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased baking dish. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: "easy" pasta salads
directions: Cook tortellini as per directions on package.
Cut up broccoli, tomatoes and cucumber in small pieces.
Toss in dressing.

title: buckeyes(candy)
directions: Soften margarine to room temperature.
Mix with peanut butter and add powdered sugar until well mixed and can be kneaded.
Knead until smooth and pinch small amounts off.
Roll into balls.
Set on wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Refrigerate about 1 hour.

title: stir-fry rice and beef
directions: Cut meat into thin slices.
Cut onion into wedges and pepper into thin strips.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in wok over high heat; add meat and garlic.
Stir-fry until meat is brown and tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove from wok.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in wok over medium-high heat.
Add onion and pepper.
Stir-fry until tender-crisp, about 2 minutes.
Add meat and rice to vegetables. Combine all remaining ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour over rice, meat and vegetables. Stir-fry until mixed well.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: popcorn
directions: Get out an oven mitt; then all you need to do is get an electric oven and put the popcorn in.
Push the button that says popcorn on it and watch it pop.
You don't need butter because it already has butter on it.
Use the popcorn in a big box with a picture of butter splashing on it.
But remember to take the popcorn out of the box before you put it in the oven.

title: potato cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar together.
Add all other ingredients and beat until smooth. Bake in greased and floured tube pan about 50 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix chicken, sour cream and soup together; pour into casserole dish.
Mix poppy seeds, butter and crackers.
Spread on top of chicken mixture.
Cover with foil and bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: stewed jack rabbit and dumplings
directions: Thaw rabbit.
Cut into serving size pieces.
Simmer giblets in saucepan in 2 cups of water.
Slice and dice salt pork.
Brown salt pork over medium-high heat.
Brown the rabbit pieces in the pork fat; be careful of spattering fat.
This will take 10 to 15 minutes.
Add liquid from saucepan.
