Put in Dutch oven and bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 300° to 350°.

title: holiday green beans
directions: Mix in 2 to 3-quart casserole the well drained green beans, almonds, mushrooms and 1/3 of the onion rings.
In a small mixing bowl, whisk together the milk and soup until smooth.
Pour the soup mixture over the beans.
Cover casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove lid.
Sprinkle remaining onion rings on surface of beans and bake another 10 minutes uncovered.
This recipe is very forgiving of time and temperature.
(Sliced water chestnuts may be substituted for almonds.)

title: vegetable soup with cheese
directions: Cook on low until vegetables are tender.
Add 2 cups milk and 2 tablespoons oleo.
If needed to be thick, add 2 tablespoons flour to part of milk; mix with hot ingredients.
Add 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese.

title: mock crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into cakes.
Fry in oil in large frying pan, until brown on both side.
Drain and serve.

title: pea soup
directions: Cook the carrot, soup, peas, water, onion and ham bone for 45 minutes or more.
Add the milk and salt and pepper.

title: nacho dip
directions: Cut Velveeta cheese into cubes.
Add cream cheese and sour cream.
Microwave until creamed, stirring occasionally.
For best results, keep warm in small crock-pot.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add 1/4 of the flour at a time and beat until smooth. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Invert pan on rack and leave until cool.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Cut zucchini into chunks.
Combine all ingredients in pot. Boil for 30 minutes.
Put in blender and puree.
Add 1 carton whipping cream.
Serve cold or hot.
Can freeze and reheat.

title: stir-fry canadian bacon and vegetables
directions: *Any combination:
Green pepper, mushrooms, celery, pea pods, broccoli, cauliflower, water chestnuts, green beans, etc.

title: pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven.
Prepare cake according to package in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon over apples. Mix flour, butter and 1/2 cup sugar until it looks like bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over pie and bake at about 350° until apples are tender.

title: spicy turkey roast
directions: Remove mesh from the turkey.
Lay turkey out as flat as possible on a cutting board, placing skin side down.
Combine the garlic, rosemary, pepper and salt in the work bowl of food processor with blade in place, or in blender.
Turn motor on.
Add oil, processing until coarsely chopped.
Spread half the garlic mixture over the inside of the turkey.
Re-roll turkey.
Tie firmly with string every 2 inches to return meat to its original log shape.
Spread evenly with the remaining garlic mixture.

title: kids' tropical treat
directions: Wrap banana in foil and place it in the freezer for 1/2 hour. Remove and place all ingredients in a blender and puree for 30 seconds or until it is smooth.
Pour in small paper cups.
Makes 5 servings.
Children love these.

title: icebox cheese cake
directions: Line pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) with crumb mixture and pack. Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water and let cool.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Add to Jell-O mixture.
Have milk cold; whip until stiff and add Jell-O and cream mixture.
Whip 3 or 4 minutes and add drained crushed pineapple.
Mix well.
Pour into pan and sprinkle about 1 cup crumbs on top.
Then refrigerate until firm (overnight).

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix cans of hot sauce together.
Peel avocados and mash with fork.
Add hot sauce to taste and seasoned pepper and lemon pepper to taste.

title: hot hominy
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in a casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Put in uncooked pie shell.
I usually cover crust edges with aluminum foil, because they will get too brown before the pie gets done.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Pie is usually done when any small crack appears on the top layer of nuts.

title: mexican surprise
directions: Saute meat and onions; drain.
Add canned ingredients and spices; simmer, stirring constantly.
Line casserole dish with Doritos.
Pour ingredients over chips and top with grated cheese. Heat in a 350° oven or microwave until cheese bubbles.
Serve with Doritos.

title: chris's b~b~q hot dogs(firemen supper favorite)
directions: Combine everything and place into a crock-pot. Simmer on low until hot.

title: kielbasa bean soup
directions: In large saucepan, bring ingredients to boil.
Reduce heat. Simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening in bowl until light and fluffy. Add sugar gradually.
Blend in egg yolks.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk mixed with the soda.
Stir in vanilla, walnuts and coconut.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Put into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° until cake pulls from side of pan.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, eggs, oil and cinnamon.
Add flour mixture, then fold in apples and nuts.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Dice cheese and add to undiluted soup and heat slowly until cheese melts.
Add sour cream and pepper sauce.
Stir until hot and pour into serving dish (small crock-pot).
Sprinkle with chili powder and serve warm with chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water; drain and set aside.
Cut up mushrooms and saute 15 minutes.
Combine croutons with mushrooms 5 minutes.
Put croutons and mushrooms on the bottom of a lightly greased casserole dish.
Put broccoli on top.
Pour mushroom soup over broccoli and lay cheese on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple, bananas, nuts and strawberries.
Pour 1/2 in oblong glass pan and jell.
Leave remainder on cabinet.
After it has jelled, spread sour cream over first layer.
Then pour rest of jello mixture on top and refrigerate for about 2 hours.

title: minestrone
directions: Rinse and soak navy beans according to package instructions; discard water and add fresh water.
Cook according to package instructions, omitting salt; set aside.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook all together until onions are glossy.
Lower fire.
Add 1 can tomato paste and 2 cans water.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Fold into cooked rice (1 cup when raw).
Pack into casserole dish and add 1 can tomato soup diluted with 1/2 can water.
Mix and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Crumble ground beef in 2-quart casserole dish.
Cook in microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Drain.
Top with Tater Tots, corn, peas and onion.
Pour cream of celery soup, then golden mushroom soup on top.
Bake in microwave on High for 10 minutes. Turn dish halfway through cooking time.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan praline candy
directions: Cook sugar, milk, syrup and margarine until it forms a soft ball in water.
Remove from heat and cool until lukewarm.
Add pecans and vanilla and beat until stiff.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: not your average strawberry trifle
directions: Combine frozen strawberries, liqueur and Marsala in a saucepan and boil down until thickened.
Stir to prevent scorching on bottom.
Cool.
Prepare pudding and milk as directed.
Whip cream until stiff.
Fold pudding and cream together, cover and refrigerate.
Wash, hull and slice strawberries; keeping the nicest ones whole for garnish.
Sweeten and whip whipping cream for garnish.
Toast, if desired, slivered almonds for garnish.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Bake for 35 minutes in a quick oven at 450°.

title: hot potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and corn flakes.
Put into a greased casserole dish.
Spread corn flakes on top.
Drizzle butter over corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or longer until golden brown.
Serves 12.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: This dessert is made in layers and is the best.

title: punch
directions: Mix good pineapple juice, Kool-Aid and sugar.
Dissolve sugar in hot water.
Put in gallon jug.
Add pineapple juice and Kool-Aid.
Mix good, then finish filling jug with cold water. Makes 1 gallon.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
When dissolved, add 1 cup of cold water and salt.
Grind together the cranberries and orange; add sugar and apples.
Combine with jello; chill.

title: sugarless applesauce cake
directions: Cook raisins until all of the water is boiled out. Add the applesauce, sweetener, oil and eggs; mix well. Blend in the flour, baking soda, cinnamon and vanilla. Pour the mixture into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake is done.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine these ingredients and boil 2 minutes; to be used as a basting for loaf.

title: lemon cream cheese pound cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat sugar, butter and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in lemon juice, flavorings and salt.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and beat well until smooth.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 12-cup tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown.
Test to see if a wooden toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack in pan 10 minutes. Then invert on rack to cool completely.
Then glaze.

title: white cake
directions: Add 1/2 cup of milk to the mix and beat 2 minutes.
Add remainder of milk, egg whites and flavoring; beat 2 minutes.
Pour into two waxed paper-lined 8-inch layer pans.
Be sure to grease the sides of the pan.
Bake in a moderate 375° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a small bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, nutmeg and salt.
Set aside.

title: carol monroe's squash casserole
directions: Brown bacon; saute green onion.
Cook squash with salt, pepper and seasoned salt to taste.
Beat eggs and mix with sour cream. Add bacon and squash to mixture.
Grease large casserole dish. Pour one-half mixture in bottom of dish, add one-half of both cheeses.
Add remaining mixture and top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Put vegetables in serving bowl in layers; spread salad dressing on top.
Sprinkle cheese and Bac*Os on top of dressing. Cover and chill overnight.
Mix when ready to serve.

title: chicken noodle salad
directions: Boil macaroni until tender, drain.
Mix in chicken, mayonnaise, salt, pepper, mushrooms and peas.
Serves 4 to 6. Serve with toast or crackers.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef, onions and pepper.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce; mix well.
Add garlic powder, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper.
Stir in Cheddar cheese and macaroni.
Pour into large baking dish.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and your favorite toppings.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: one pan pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease rectangular baking dish, 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inches.
Mix baking mix, milk and eggs in dish with fork until batter is of uniform color (batter will be lumpy).
Stir in pepperoni, 1 cup cheese, the green pepper, onion, oregano, basil and garlic powder.
Spread evenly.
Bake until top is light brown, about 30 minutes.
Spread with pizza sauce and sprinkle with mushrooms and 1 cup cheese.
Bake just until cheese is melted, 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lucille's easy tomato aspic
directions: Heat 3/4 cup tomato juice plus vinegar.
Stir in Jell-O until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and chill until firm.

title: devilicious party spread
directions: Using an electric mixer, mix softened cream cheese, deviled ham and Worcestershire sauce.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in by hand the green and red pepper and cayenne pepper.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Whip for about 5 minutes.
Pour into a pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Cool, then enjoy.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into flowerets.
If stems are tender, slice and add these.
Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours or make 1 day in advance.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Beat together well the oleo, sugar and eggs, until fluffy. Stir together well the flour, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves, allspice and nutmeg.
Add flour mixture and applesauce, all at once, to egg mixture.
Stir together.
Beat on medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until center tests done.
Frost with cream cheese icing.

title: apple sauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs; sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture with applesauce, beating after each addition.
If batter seems to be a little stiff, add 1/4 to 1/2 c. milk.
Stir in raisins, nuts and dates.
Bake in greased and floured 10 inch tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheerios treats
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Microwave margarine on High 45 seconds.
Add marshmallows; toss to coat with margarine. Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth when stirred, stirring after 45 seconds.
Stir in peanut butter.
Immediately add cereal; mix lightly until well coated.
Using greased spatula or wax paper, press mixture into prepared pan.
Cool; cut into squares.
Makes about 24.

title: dieter's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Sift together the dry ingredients. Cream butter. Add sugar substitute, vanilla and egg, blending well. Stir in chocolate pieces. Drop by level teaspoon onto a lightly greased baking dish. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: crock pot green beans
directions: Drain beans.
Place in crock pot.
Top with sliced onion and crumbled bacon.
In small sauce pan, combine bacon grease, sugar, vinegar and water.	Bring to boil and pour over beans.
Cook on low 4 or 5 hours.
If you do not have a crock pot, cook in dutch oven for 45 minutes.

title: mandarin orange congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add undiluted orange juice and the mandarin oranges and juice.
Refrigerate until set.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar.
Add flour, nuts and flavoring; mix well.
Bake in a 300° oven slowly for 25 to 30 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: paw paw's stew
directions: Do not substitute or omit anything!!!

title: cake mix brownie
directions: Combine egg, oil and water.
Add dry cake mix and blend. Press gently in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan where only the bottom is greased.
Bake 25 minutes in an oven preheated to 350°.
Batter will be very thick and sticky.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken breasts in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Pork chops may be substituted for chicken.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing mix with melted margarine and put half in the bottom of casserole dish (reserve half for top).
Mix chicken, soup, sour cream and 1 cup of broth together and put on top of crumbs.
Sprinkle remaining cornbread stuffing on top of this and pour on the other 1/2 cup broth.
Bake at 350° until brown (30 to 45 minutes).
Good.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze all water from spinach.
Mix all together. Refrigerate until cool.

title: burger casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Mix in corn, tomato soup, water and egg.
Pour in buttered
dish
and top with 1/2 cup crushed cracker crumbs.
Cook in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ham and cheese bread
directions: Roll thawed bread dough into a rectangle approximately 1 foot long, 6-inches wide.
Layer ham and cheese down center.
Fold long ends of bread toward center.
Pinch shut, then fold ends to middle of loaf.
Pinch shut.
Place in greased bread pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°, then take out and put slits in top.
Bake another 20 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Saute onion in butter; add shrimp and cook until shrimp are done.
Chop shrimp if they are large.
Put in the softened cream cheese.
Mix well; add
mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning.
In a 9 x 12-inch pan, layer bean dip first.
Second add sour cream mixture.
Top with tomato, green onion, shredded cheese and black olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and with knife remove stems and inside of mushrooms.
Chop stems and set aside (preheat oven to 375°).

title: teenage punch
directions: Combine and chill until very cold.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco, then add milk, flour, eggs, baking soda, all spices, salt, zucchini and nuts.
Grease and flour pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: green bean stew in crock-pot
directions: Layer round steak at bottom of crock-pot and season with Lawry's salt generously.
Layer carrot slices and green beans, then spread mushroom soup over the top of green beans, but not touching the walls of the pot.
Cook on high for 4 1/2 hours. Season with pepper before serving or just season individual servings at the table.
Serve with noodles.

title: brown sugar chews
directions: Mix brown sugar, vanilla and egg.
Then add flour, salt and soda.
Mix.
Add walnuts.
Bake at 350° in greased 9-inch square pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven as soon as solid.
Cool. Cut in squares.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: ranch style eggs
directions: In a small skillet heat 2 teaspoons oil.
Holding tortillas with tongs, dip in hot oil until limp (10 seconds).
Line a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish with tortillas.
Keep warm.

title: mom's southern potato salad
directions: Place potatoes, water and salt in a large pan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until fork-tender.
Refrigerate potatoes until cool; peel.
Chop potatoes and 5 eggs; reserve remaining egg for garnish. Combine sugar, salt, pepper, mustard, pickles, onion and mayonnaise in large bowl.
Quarter or slice reserved egg; garnish top of salad.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 7 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Slice peaches and spread on the bottom of a 9 inch x 9 inch x 3/4 inch pan.
Combine sugar, 2 Tbsp. flour and cinnamon and sprinkle on peaches. Dot with butter.
Mix together 1 c. sifted flour, salt, butter, oil, egg, baking powder and milk.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: stir-fried broccoli
directions: Stir-fry the broccoli
in
the oil.
Add 1/4 cup water, salt and sugar.
Cover and cook 2 minutes.
Uncover and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: hash brown bake
directions: Mix frozen hash browns, sour cream, soup, chips and cheese (reserve some cheese for topping) together.
Brown butter and onion; add to hash browns.
Place in deep 9 x 13-inch baking dish for 45 minutes at 375°.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top for 5 minutes before done.

title: mexican relish
directions: Grind the vegetables and mix with the salt.
Let drain in colander several hours or overnight.
Mix mustard seed, vinegar and sugar and stir into ground vegetables.
Put mixture in sterilized pint jars.
Put on canning lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 to 10 minutes to seal.

title: 15-minute super sundae pie
directions: Melt buttah ... add chips ... heat, till chips are melted ... add remainin' ingredients ... mix 'n pour in an unbaked pie shell ... bake at 350° fur 45 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Beat eggs, blend in sour cream, sugar, oil and corn.
Blend cornmeal, salt and baking powder and add to mixture.
Blend and pour into greased pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: sour cream cherry nut cake
directions: Soften butter (or margarine).
Add sugar and beat.
Beat in eggs.
Add sour cream; mix until creamy.
Add all dry ingredients; mix well.
Add almond and vanilla extracts; mix.
Fold in nuts and cherries.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolates.
Beat 2 minutes, then stir in chocolates.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Crumble beef into slow-cooking pot.
Add pepper, oregano, basil, seasoned salt and dry soup mix.
Stir in water, tomato sauce and soy sauce.
Then add celery and carrots.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Turn control to high, add cooked macaroni and Parmesan cheese.
Cover and cook on high for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Combine all ingredients for crunch in a lager bowl. Mix well. Place in greased 3 qt. Pyrex dish.

title: mrs. britton's pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar with spoon, then add the eggs.
Mix well.
Add the salt and syrup to butter mixture and cook over hot water for 5 minutes.
Then add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no bake english trifle
directions: Make vanilla pudding according to directions and set aside. Make Jell-O according to directions and set aside.
Slice pound cake thin to line 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour strawberry Jell-O while warm over cake.
Spread pineapple over strawberry Jell-O.
Pour vanilla pudding over pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding. Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, place strawberries over Cool Whip.
Makes 12 servings.

title: georgia nuggets
directions: Mix brown sugar
and whipping cream over low heat until sugar has dissolved.
Cook
over	medium	heat until soft ball stage. Cool.
Put	margarine
and	vanilla flavoring in candy mixture. Add nuts
and beat until candy starts to harden. Drop by spoon on wax paper.	Allow to completely cool before taking off wax paper.

title: easy oven stew
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika in a paper bag.
Drop in beef. Shake until coated.
Mix with Wesson oil in 3-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes.
Stir 1 time. Add vegetables, water and tomato sauce.
Mix, cover and bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together sugar, salt, flour, baking soda and baking powder.
In another bowl mix the eggs and oil.
Beat well. Combine the two mixtures and blend well with electric mixer.
Add carrots and vanilla and blend.
Pour into greased and floured layer cake pans and bake in 325° oven for about 35 minutes.

title: chelle's casserole
directions: Mix meat, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Lightly pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange potatoes over meat.
Combine soup and milk; pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° until sauce is bubbly and potatoes are golden brown, about 45 minutes.
If using potatoes frozen, increase baking time accordingly.
Inexpensive, delicious and fills the house with a wonderful aroma.

title: minestrone soup(for nonfat diets)
directions: Cook all ingredients, except macaroni, for 1 1/2 hours.
Add elbows the last 1/2 hour.
Add kidney beans and chickpeas if wanted.
Can be frozen in small containers to be used as needed. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese when serving.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Grease bottom only of 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients; beat for 30 seconds.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350° or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except green onions.
Mix well and chill.
Garnish with green onions.
Serve with fresh vegetables. Yields 2 cups.

title: aunt margaret's peppernuts
directions: Mix the ingredients and roll into ropes.
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces and bake 7 minutes in 400° oven.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cover and refrigerate. Serve on lettuce leaf with a slice of tomato or cut a whole tomato into 4 wedges and fill center with cottage cheese.

title: cold green bean salad
directions: Drain beans and peas.
Add pimento and onion. Mix the salt, sugar, water, oil and vinegar.
Pour over other ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.
Pour off liquid when ready to serve.

title: quick and easy lasagna
directions: Brown beef and mix with sauce.
Grease two 9 x 13-inch baking dishes.
Cover bottom of pan with 1/3 of the lasagna,
top with 1/3 of the sauce and 1/3 of each cheese.
Repeat layers. The top layer should be sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes and serve.

title: spaghetti amore
directions: You will need a large ovensafe baking dish.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, Ricotta, eggs and sugar together until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients and mix all together.
Set oven at 350°.
Grease pan well.
Bake for 1 hour.
Turn stove off and leave in oven for 1 more hour.

title: tasty fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Mix 2 cups fruit juice with vanilla pudding. Cook on medium heat until thick.
Cool and pour over fruit.
Mix well and serve.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat yolks until thick.
Add milk and mix.
Add Key lime juice and continue to mix.
Pour into a graham cracker crust and bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.

title: cuervo after hours
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Blend until ice is crushed and drink is frosty.
Pour into pewter cups or chilled champagne saucers.
Dust with additional cinnamon, if desired. Makes 2 drinks.

title: four o'clock cookies
directions: Mix together.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet with teaspoon. Watch closely while baking.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
These are scrumptuous!

title: cranberry banana salad
directions: Wash
and
pick over cranberries, discarding soft ones. Add water,
cover
and	cook slowly until berries are tender, about 20	minutes.
Stir in sugar and cook for 2 minutes more until liquid forms a syrup.
Remove from heat and rub berries through a sieve.
Then carefully stir in diced bananas.
Cool, then
chill in	refrigerator until jellied.
Cut into squares and lift into lettuce cups.
Serves 5.

title: watergate salad(pistachio salad)
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Roll biscuit out flat and wrap hot dog with biscuits with ends out. Bake at 375° until biscuit is golden brown. Remove from oven and top with cheese. Put back in oven for 2 or 3 minutes to let cheese melt.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Mix cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Add eggs; mix until blended. Mix crumbs, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar. Press into 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Pour batter over crust. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight. Cut into bars.

title: skillet beans
directions: Cook and stir bacon and onion in 10-inch skillet until bacon is crisp.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally, until liquid is absorbed, 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: honey chews
directions: Bring butter and honey to a boil and boil to 260° on candy thermometer or to the hard-ball stage.
Remove from heat and add chopped dates and nuts.
Stir for 2 minutes, then pour into buttered pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
May be wrapped in cellophane for gift giving or to store.

title: italian baked beans
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery.
Brown sausage and bacon and drain.
Mix all beans, sauce, onion, pepper, celery, sausage, bacon and barbecue sauce.
Mix well.
Bake in covered roaster at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
This recipe will serve 15 or 20 people.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute onions in butter.
In saucepan, combine onions, broth, potatoes and seasonings. Cook, covered, about 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes cook through. Add corn and milk.
Heat through.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and oleo.
Cover and let stand at least 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into a well-greased pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: mommy's rolled butterscotch cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and set aside. Cream margarine or butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Chill until dough is firm enough to roll.
Roll 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut with floured cookie cutter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 5 to 6 minutes in 425° oven.
Yields 7 dozen cookies.

title: sweet potato pies
directions: Put cooked potatoes in mixing bowl while hot.
Add cream cheese and butter; mix well.
Add sugar and eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla and beat on high until all lumps are out.
Bake at 300° or 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: helen's favorite lime sherbet
directions: Boil sugar and water together until it forms a thick syrup. Add salt, allow mixture to cool.
Add cream, lime juice and vanilla; freeze.
Makes 6 quarts.
This is for a 6-quart freezer.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except crescent rolls, and mix together.
Take 2 crescent rolls and press together at seam to make flat rectangle.
Place a scoop of chicken mixture (about 1/4 cup).
Bring 4 corners up together to meet.
Bring and pinch seams together so that everything is closed up.
Continue process until mixture and crescent rolls are used up.

title: tv pot roast
directions: Rub pepper into
roast;
bring
oil
to
smoke and brown roast on both
sides.
Remove roast and saute celery and onions in oil. In
large
pot
combine
roast,
onions, celery, wine, tomatoes, beef stock,
salt
and cracked pepper; cover and cook slowly for 2 to
1/2 hours or until tender;
add carrots and cook about 30 minutes.
Add
potatoes
and cook until they are done.

title: oven baked chicken and vegetables
directions: Cut carrots, potato and onion into large pieces.
Wash.
In a casserole dish, place carrots, potato and onion.
Arrange chicken breast on top.
Pour water over ingredients; cover casserole. Place in preheated oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken and vegetables are tender.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Take an 8 1/2 x 11-inch roasting pan and pour soup into pan. Add milk and stir in with soup.
Add tuna fish in water; chop up in pan and mix thoroughly.
Put cooked noodles in mixture also. Combine bread crumbs in pan and mix thoroughly.
Then, flatten out mixture evenly and put thin layer of bread crumbs over the whole pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until mixture is bubbling.
Take out and serve.

title: unforgettable coleslaw
directions: Mix oil with vinegar, lemon or lime juice in a bowl.
Add mustard, celery salt and mayonnaise, mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over cabbage and mix to coat cabbage.
Sprinkle paprika on top to dress up for serving.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk and melted oleo. Place fruit in the bottom of the oiled pan.
Pour batter over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix cranberry sauce, dressing and onion soup mix together with a spoon.
Place chicken in a large, covered casserole dish and pour cranberry mixture over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours, uncovered.
After 1 1/2 hours, cover.
Or, bake at 225° for 4 hours, covered.

title: bonny's potato chowder
directions: Place first seven ingredients in large pot, cover with water and cook until tender.
Scald milk until bubbles form around edge of pan.
Remove 1 1/2 cups milk; add butter and flour.
Add this mixture to rest of milk and then add to vegetable mixture.
Add cheese; stir.
Chowder will thicken.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Combine with soups, broth, green chilies and sour cream.
Add deboned chicken.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer half of the corn tortillas, then half the chicken and sauce and half the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 10.

title: una's shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter; saute pepper, onion, celery and green onions for about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste with bay leaves. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add shrimp; simmer for 15 minutes. Dissolve cornstarch in 1 pint water and add to shrimp mixture. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add lemon juice and
salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve over steaming rice or creamed potatoes.
Might add a few drops of Tabasco or red pepper.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Stir in flour, salt, mustard and pepper until smooth.
Remove from heat.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut tops off of bell peppers and remove insides.
Boil in a large pot for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from water and allow to cool.
Brown and season ground beef as desired.
Drain meat; set aside.
Prepare Rice-A-Roni mix according to package directions. Add ground beef, rice mix, 1 can of Hunt's sauce, oregano and sugar; mix well.
Place this mixture into bell peppers.
Place remaining mixture in a baking dish along with bell peppers.
Pour 1 can of Hunt's sauce over mixture; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: turnip souffle
directions: Boil turnips and carrots together until tender.
Drain well. Mash together and add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in a baking pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°

title: quick and easy salad
directions: Mix jello and cottage cheese.
Add fruit cocktail, Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together and place in buttered pan (5 x 7-inch).

title: breakfast drink
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend 10 seconds.

title: pistachio pie
directions: mix together crushed pineapple and pudding mix, add nuts and mix well.
Then add other ingredients and pour in crust and chill before serving.

title: apricot mist punch
directions: Mix together and serve chilled.

title: candied nuts
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium saucepan and stir.
Boil over medium heat until all water cooks out (about 20 to 22 minutes), stirring constantly.
The instant the nuts turn sugary, spread on cookie sheet and separate with two forks.

title: george's magic salad
directions: Pour jello powder over cottage cheese. Mix and add pineapple. Fold in
Cool Whip and chill.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, green pepper and celery.
Add tomato sauce, corn and taco seasoning; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix the cornbread mix and evaporated milk well. Pour over top of meat mixture.
Sprinkle top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake until top is golden brown.

title: rice krispy bars(sugar-free; low-fat)
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
If mixture is too dry, bars will not cut (if so, add more peanut butter). Press mixture into an 8 x 8-inch glass dish.
Cut into bars and refrigerate until ready to eat.
Delicious and sugar-free!!!!

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix cream cheese (room temperature), strawberries and pineapple together.
Fold in pecans, then bananas and then lightly fold in Cool Whip.
Place in muffin pans lined with silver cupcake holders.
Place in freezer until ready to serve, then take out about 10 minutes before ready to eat.

title: blueberry marvel
directions: Dissolve jello 2 cups in boiling water.
Add only 1 cup cold water.
Stir in pie filling.
Refrigerate until cold.

title: ham dip
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.
Also makes a good sandwich.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat the pudding and cold milk until mixture begins to thicken.
Add Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Mix well.
Slice bananas and add to mixture.
Layer in a large bowl with vanilla wafers.
Sprinkle crushed vanilla wafers on top.

title: peas and mushrooms
directions: Cook peas.
Drain well.
Cook mushrooms and onion in butter until tender.
Stir in sugar, salt and pepper.
Add cooked peas and pimento.
Cover; heat through.
Serves 4.

title: kentucky biscuits
directions: Sift all the ingredients together and make a nest.
Add most of the milk and shortening.
Squeeze the shortening, flour and milk until well mixed.
Add rest of milk, if needed, and mix.
Turn on floured board.
Knead until desired consistency.
Roll onto floured board.
Cut into desired size.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: diamond fudge
directions: Cook first three ingredients in pan over low heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture melts and is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add powdered sugar, stirring until smooth.
Put into an 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Let stand 10 minutes at room temperature before cutting.
Store in refrigerator.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer a few minutes before basting on chicken or whatever.

title: garden saute
directions: Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion, bell pepper and garlic; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add squash and zucchini, stir-fry 3 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add tomatoes and next three ingredients.
Cook 1 minute or until thoroughly heated.
Remove from heat; sprinkle with cheese.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: broken omelet
directions: Beat eggs in bowl.
Add other ingredients.
Mix together.
Put in skillet and cook at medium, until eggs are cooked.
Serves 3 people.

title: tortilla roll-ups (2)
directions: Mix together cream cheese and dressing and any of the following if desired:
green onion, black olives, cheese, broccoli, and/or slaw.
Spread mixture thinly on tortillas.
Roll up.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice in the morning.

title: glaze for ham
directions: Mix together and baste over ham last 15 minutes of cooking time.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan; line with graham crackers.
Mix pudding and milk until thick; blend in Cool Whip. Put 1/3 of pudding on crackers; cover with crackers and add 2 more layers of pudding and crackers.
Put icing (chocolate or vanilla) on crackers.
Keep in refrigerator.
Make this at least 4 hours before serving.
(Chocolate pudding can be used instead of vanilla.)
Very easy to make.

title: french cream tarts
directions: Bake small tart shells until lightly browned.
Mix cream cheese, that has been softened, with confectoiners sugar.
Mix until creamy.
Whip whipping cream.
Fold in cheese mixture.
Fill tarts.
Let set until firm.

title: pesto cheese loaf
directions: Blend the cream cheese with the butter, garlic, pistachios and salt and pepper to taste.
Line a loaf pan with damp cheesecloth (wrung out well), overlapping sides of pan.
Line with Provolone, overlapping sides of pan.
Layer as follows:
half of the pesto, add another layer of Provolone, half of the sun-dried tomatoes, cream cheese, remaining tomatoes, layer of Provolone, remaining pesto and finish with remaining Provolone.
Chill.
Unmold when firm.
Serve with baguette slices, toasted or untoasted.

title: 3-layer chocolate delight
directions: Melt margarine; mix with flour and add 1/2 of pecans.
Press in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for exactly 15 minutes (cool).
Mix softened cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1 1/2 cups of Cool Whip with electric mixer until smooth.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk until thickened.
Spread over 2nd layer.
Put remaining Cool Whip on top and sprinkle chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: mikey's pecan pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together your flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add sugar and mix well.
Make a well in the center and add your oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
After mixing well, add your nuts. Pour batter into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: corn casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Cook noodles and drain them.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour mixture into casserole dish and bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Heat oil (two inches deep) to 375° in skillet.
Beat remaining ingredients (except confectioners sugar) until smooth.
Holding forefinger over tip of 1/2-inch diameter funnel pour about 1/2 cup batter, controlling flow with finger, into hot oil, swirling it in circles from the center out.
Fry until light brown and then turn over and fry the other side.
Drain and keep warm.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Do not keep tightly covered or cakes will become soggy.
Makes approximately 6 cakes.

title: skillet cookies
directions: In an iron skillet, melt oleo.
Add sugar, dates and egg yolks.
Cook slowly for about 10 minutes, stirring constantly and mashing dates.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Make into small balls and roll in coconut.

title: light-and-easy cheesecake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in container of electric blender; process until smooth and set aside.
Start in a new bowl beating cream cheese at medium until smooth.
Add next 3 ingredients; beat until smooth.
Gradually add other mixture to new mix; beat until smooth.
It will be thin.

title: foolproof meringue
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until well blended.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until thick.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then add cooled mixture.
Beat until it reaches stiff peaks.
Pile on pie (be sure edges are sealed to crust) and brown for 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk.
Add fruit cocktail, coconut and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill for several hours.

title: marie's turtle bars
directions: Prepare the topping by mixing the softened butter with the light brown sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Continue to boil and stir for 1 minute.
Pour the cooked butter-sugar mixture over the crust and bake in a preheated 350°
oven for 20 minutes, or until the crust is lightly browned and the topping is bubbly.
Sprinkle with pecan halves.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch. Add enough milk to dissolve cornstarch. Add egg yolks. Beat well. Add remaining milk. Cook over medium heat until thickened and add vanilla, coconut and butter. Pour in baked pie shell.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add water, mayonnaise and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: two fold jello
directions: Make one Jello mix according to directions. If using fruit, drain juice and pour fruit into bottom of rectangular pan.
Pour Jello over fruit.
Pour the second dry Jello into a deep bowl. Add 1 cup boiling water.
Let stand until it starts to set.
Whip until frothy.
Add cottage cheese and whip cream into Jello. Spread on top of other Jello and refrigerate until set.

title: egg custard
directions: Boil milk, sugar and butter together for 2 minutes.
Beat egg and add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake in an unbaked pie shell at 375°.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Heat evaporated milk and marshmallows over low heat in a heavy saucepan.
Stir constantly until all the marshmallows have dissolved.
Remove from heat; add crushed crackers.
Mix well and let cool enough so you could mix with hands.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pack in pound cake pan that has been lightly greased with butter.
Refrigerate.
To remove from pan, place bottom of pan in warm water for a few minutes.

title: friendship pea soup
directions: Boil water and peas 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 1 hour.
Next, add ham, onion, pepper, marjoram, sausage, salt and parsley.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Add celery, carrots and potatoes.
Cover and cook 45 minutes.
Add flour to thicken, if needed.

title: string-bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans and stewed tomatoes.
Reserve liquid. Reduce liquid to 1 cup.
Cut bacon into small pieces and fry until crisp.
Add butter to bacon and fat.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add 1 cup liquid plus milk, chopped onions and the vegetables.
Put in casserole, topped with buttered bread crumbs. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Add alternately to mixture the flour and buttermilk.
Stir in food coloring.
Stir together vinegar and soda.
When mixture stops foaming, add to batter and mix in well.
Pour batter into cake pans and bake until done, about 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and sugar until it is a small crumb consistency.
Prepare pudding according to package directions. Pour part of crumbs into pie shell.
Pour half of pudding over crumbs.
Pour remaining crumbs and top with remaining pudding. Spread with whipped topping.
Refrigerate 8 to 12 hours before serving.

title: easy chocolate lover's cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Beat cream cheese and sugar in large bowl with mixer until well blended. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well. Stir in 1 2/3 cups chocolate chips. Pour into crust. Bake 10 minutes without opening door. Reduce temperature to 250°. Continue baking for 30 minutes. Cool completely. Cover and refrigerate until chilled. Place remaining 1/3 cup chips and whipping cream in bowl and microwave for 20 to 30 seconds or until mixture is smooth. Cool slightly. Spread over top of cheesecake. Refrigerate 15 minutes until set.

title: hot frosted gingerbread
directions: Melt butter with hot coffee.
Beat eggs.
Stir in sugar and molasses.
Combine with warm mixture.
Stir in flour and ginger to make soft drop batter.
Stir in baking powder.
Spread dough on greased, floured cookie sheet.
Bake 25 minutes in a 350° oven. While, hot, frost with 1 cup confectioners sugar mixed with 4 teaspoons cream.

title: company casserole
directions: Pan-fry onion in oil.
Add beef, salt and pepper.
Cook until pink disappears.
Add tomato sauce.
Remove from heat.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Mix together cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, green pepper and green onion. In a 3-quart casserole, spread half of the noodles.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Top with remaining noodles.
Pour meat sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
May be frozen and baked later.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: *Leave out of refrigerator overnight.

title: top of the stove casserole
directions: In large skillet coated with spray, saute turkey, garlic, onion and pepper until turkey is no longer pink.
Add zucchini and saute 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes, stock, noodles and poultry seasoning.
Cover and simmer 10 to 12 minutes or until noodles are cooked.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Garnish.

title: chocolate bavarian with caramelized almonds
directions: Beat egg yolks with 1/2 cup of the sugar until light colored and fluffy.
Combine milk, chocolate and gelatin in saucepan; stir over medium heat until gelatin is dissolved and chocolate melted. Gradually beat into egg mixture.
Chill until it begins to thicken, stirring occasionally.

title: pig in a blanket
directions: Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles.
Press perforations to seal.
Combine cheese and oregano; sprinkle over dough.
Cut each strip in half.
Place a sausage link on each square; roll up. Cut each into 3 pieces.
Secure each with a toothpick.
Place, cut side down, on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Refrigerate any leftovers. Yield: 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: grandma briley's chicken casserole
directions: Line bottom of a greased casserole dish with pieces of chicken. Top with the celery soup and the mushroom soup.
Put the margarine on top of the soup (in pieces).
Mix together in a separate bowl the Bisquick and milk.
Put the Bisquick mixture on top of the chicken mixture.
Bake until done (about 35 minutes) in a 325° oven.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in quarters.
In plastic bag, mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Shake quartered biscuits a few at a time in a bag and layer in greased Bundt pan.
In saucepan, bring to a boil so lightly thick, 1/2 cup sugar, oleo and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Turn over onto plate immediately after baking.

title: texas meatballs and rice
directions: Mix meat, egg, chili powder, salt and pepper and shape in 2-inch balls and put in casserole.
Microwave on High 7 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and microwave 7 more minutes. Let stand until rice is tender for 3 minutes.

title: millionaire salad
directions: Lightly mix all ingredients.
This is better if refrigerated overnight.

title: creamed tacos
directions: Cook hamburger and drain all grease.
Cut cheese and add tomatoes and green chilies.
Cook about 1/2 hour or cook one hour in the crock-pot.
About 30 minutes before serving, add 1/2 pint of whipping cream.
Stir often.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Stir in water. Cook over medium heat until thick and clear.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Cool.
Pour part of glaze in bottom of pie shell.
Add berries.
Press berries down tight and add rest of glaze.
Chill.

title: polynesian carrots
directions: Cook carrots in butter 10 minutes.
Add other ingredients. Mix and serve.

title: green and gold casserole
directions: Combine spinach, water chestnuts and 1/3 of Welsh rarebit in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Spread remaining rarebit evenly over all.
Top with onion rings.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 15 minutes or until heated through.

title: pineapple coconut cake
directions: Combine all ingredients
and
pour into 2 (9-inch) or 3 (8-inch) layer pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Frost and fill with special icing.

title: caramel
directions: Melt 1 cup sugar in iron skillet. Stir about 25 minutes (turns honey color). Add butter, 1 cup sugar and the milk.
Mix. Add 1 cup sugar. Cook slowly until it forms into a firm ball. Cool. Beat.
Add pecans.
Cut the next day.

title: blackened redfish(you may substitute catfish for the redfish)
directions: In a small dish, stir together the paprika, salt, onion powder, garlic powder, red pepper, white pepper, black pepper, oregano and thyme; set aside.
Melt the margarine (or butter).
Dip the fish in melted oleo or butter, then sprinkle each side with about 1 teaspoon of spice mixture.
Place the coated fish in a single layer on a platter.
Place fish in a very hot skillet in which you have melted a little butter.
Keep skillet hot and cook until fish flakes with a fork (approximately 2 minutes on each side).
Each side will look black.
This causes quite a bit of smoke.
Some people prefer cooking this outside.

title: cheese stuffed chicken
directions: Rinse and pat dry chicken.
Use a sharp knife; cut small pocket in side of each breast.
Insert cheese slice in pocket.
In a small bowl beat egg white slightly.
In another bowl stir together flour, Parmesan cheese, parsley and paprika.
Dip chicken in egg, then coat with flour mixture.
Spray 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking pan or dish.
Arrange chicken in dish and bake in a 375° oven 20 to 25 minutes, until chicken is tender and not pink.

title: fiesta corn dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Season to taste.
Chill and serve with tortilla chips.
Dip keeps well for several days in the refrigerator.

title: mrs. nixon's hot chicken salad
directions: Bake 20 minutes in oven or until cheese is melted.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: quick mexican lasagne
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Mix with spaghetti sauce and wine. Mix cheeses.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package; drain.
Mix all ingredients; pour into a 9 x 9-inch dish.
Top with crushed cheese Ritz crackers or bread crumbs.
If using bread crumbs, use margarine to prepare them.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: marinated pickles or beets
directions: Mix together and keep in refrigerator at least overnight.

title: congressional bean soup
directions: In large pan, heat beans in water.
Boil gently for 2 minutes; turn off heat and let stand 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and cook until beans are very soft.
Remove bay leaf and ham bone.
Cut meat off bone; return meat to beans.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
(Can cover and cook low for 12 to 14 hours until beans are soft in a slow cooker.)

title: lazy pie
directions: Melt butter in pan. While oven is heating, mix dry ingredients.
Pour milk into dry mixture and stir until smooth. Pour batter over melted butter, but do not mix.
Pour cherries or favorite fruit over batter and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Be sure fruit is drained. I use an 8-inch square Pyrex dish.

title: fried soup
directions: Shake all of vegetables, flour and cornmeal in a large container until vegetables are coated.
Heat oil in a large skillet until hot, add vegetables and cook until tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Beat eggs and flour until smooth.
Mix in rest of ingredients. Pour into well-greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: two cheese kugel
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat cheeses until smooth. Add beaten eggs, sugar and vanilla. Add cooked noodles and blend thoroughly. Pour melted butter into noodle mixture and stir.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 45 minutes until lightly browned.

title: broccoli and cauliflower bake
directions: Cook vegetables.
Mix all ingredients and top with onion rings.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: nuts over turkey
directions: Combine 1st 7 ingredients.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with almonds.
Makes 6 half cup servings (300 calories).

title: five minute miracle
directions: Blend fruit cocktail juice and 1 package dry lemon jello instant pudding.
Pour over ingredients and chill.
Good with meat or fowl.
Also a great light dessert.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion; add spices, sauce, tomatoes and olives. Mix egg with cottage cheese and set aside.
Soften tortillas in heated oil and cut in half or quarters.
In a large casserole or 13 x 9-inch baking dish, spread 1/3 meat sauce, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese and 1/2 tortillas.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining meat mixture, Cheddar cheese and tortilla chips. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: aimee's spaghetti sauce recipe
directions: In skillet brown meat; drain fat.
In a large pot, lightly saute chopped onion and garlic in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Add ground turkey or beef and simmer 1/2 to 1 hour on low heat.

title: sunny delight
directions: Place 3 scoops of sherbet into a tall glass.
Pour 8 ounces of nectar into the glass.
Stir a little.
Add a spoon and a straw.

title: lemon cheese filling
directions: Combine all ingredients, except margarine, in saucepan and cook until thick, stirring constantly to prevent sticking.
Then add margarine and set off heat to cool.
Will frost 3 layer cake. Freezes well.

title: low-fat cherry cheese cake
directions: In bowl, mix sour cream, pudding mix and Cool Whip. Add about 2 tablespoons of cherry pie filling and mix together. Pour into crust.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Cook the crushed pineapple, sugar and flour until thick. Slice bananas into cooled pie shell to line bottom.
Add to cooled pineapple mixture the grated coconut and chopped nuts.
Pour mixture over bananas in pie shell.
Let stand in refrigerator until cold.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream before serving.

title: embutido
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients on a piece of cheesecloth.
Spread the mixture.
Arrange sliced pickles, hard-cooked eggs and sausages on mixture.
Roll into shape and wrap.
Tie both ends. Sew or tie the opening.
Cover with broth and simmer until done. Cool and unwrap before slicing.
Serve with tomato sauce.

title: apricot dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Beat at medium speed 4 minutes.
Put instant pie filling in bottom of 8-inch square pan. Put cake mixture on top of filling.
Sprinkle with nuts, oleo and coconut, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.
Can use any pie filling.

title: picnic rice salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first seven ingredients. In a small bowl, combine the Miracle Whip, sweet pickle relish, salad dressing, salt and pepper. Fold into rice mixture. Serve in a lettuce lined bowl. Refrigerate leftovers. Yield: 4-6 servings. I do not put mine in a lettuce lined bowl.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 5 ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain noodles.
Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Layer half the noodles in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread with half the cottage cheese mixture.
Add half the Mozzarella cheese and half the meat sauce. Repeat.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: 24 hour pea salad
directions: Cover layers with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Add grated Monterey Jack cheese and crinkled bacon on top of salad. Before serving, add chopped green onions on salad.
Toss right before you eat.
Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours before serving.

title: bryon's polish beet soup
directions: In a 4-quart kettle or pressure cooker, place the bones, water, salt and onion.
Cook covered for 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours or until meat is falling off the bones in kettle or for 30 minutes after 15 pounds pressure is reached in a pressure cooker.
Strain broth and place in kettle with beets.
Cook, covered, until beets are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Strip meat from bones and add meat to soup. When beets are tender, add vinegar and mix well.
Combine sour cream, water and flour in a bowl with a wire whisk or in a blender. Slowly add to the boiling soup, stirring constantly, until soup returns to boil and thickens.
Serve hot with sour cream over boiled potatoes, if potatoes are desired.
Without the potatoes, makes about 15 cups or 10 servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute broccoli, onions and carrots with margarine until tender.
Add flour for thickening.
Add broth mix with milk.
Add cheese last and cook until cheese melts and thickens.

title: cajun creole
directions: Cut corn lengthwise through less than half of corn kernel.
Cut second time to remove of grain (don't cut deeply into the corn cob).
In a heavy skillet, combine oil, corn, tomatoes and seasonings.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes, stirring to keep from sticking.
Cover and let stand for a few minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pineapple brunch casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Combine biscuit mix, milk, eggs, butter, mustard, onion powder and nutmeg in blender.
Stir in ham, cheese, onions and pineapple.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch or 12 x 7-inch pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°, until set.

title: bow tie cabbage salad
directions: In a jar with tight fitting lid, combine the first 7 ingredients.
Shake well.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.

title: lemon and lime cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box; divide mix into 2 round 9-inch cake pans. Mix jello powder (lime in one, lemon in the other). Bake and let cool. Put Cool Whip on top of bottom layer stack. Place Cool Whip all over the rest of the cake; refrigerate until ready to serve. Very, very good.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat eggs with milk. Add 1 tablespoon of melted Crisco and the corn.
Combine lightly. Deep-fry until browned.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Crumble beef into a shallow 2 1/2-quart heat resistant non-metallic casserole dish. Sprinkle meat with minced onion and crushed garlic. Heat, uncovered, on roast for 6 minutes. Stir occasionally to break up meat. Drain excess fat; add pepper, chilli powder, water and tomato sauce. Stir to combine. Heat, uncovered, for 5 minutes on roast. Alternately layer tortillas, meat sauce and cheese in a round 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Last layer should be cheese. Heat, covered, on roast for 9 to 11 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: mini fruit topped cheesecakes
directions: You will need 12 paper muffin cups.

title: casserole sauce mix
directions: Shake ingredients in a jar.
Measure 1/3 cup of mixture with 1 1/2 cups water.
Cook and stir until thick.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together butter, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Roll into balls.
Chill.
In a double boiler, melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls (on end of toothpick) into chocolate 2/3 of the way up.
Gently push out toothpick hole.
Refrigerate.

title: hello dollies
directions: Mix together butter and crumbs.
Press mixture firmly into the bottom of a 9x13-inch pan.
Add layer of coconut, chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour milk over top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in a greased casserole dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place a piece of cheese on each piece of meat.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over meat.
Toss stuffing mix in melted butter. Pour mix over soup.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake for 15 more minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: taffy pumpkin pie(the secret is the crust!)
directions: Heat the milk and water together and add to all other ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour in crust.
Continue baking at 350° for 50 minutes or until center is set but still soft.
Do not overbake.

title: rudolph's nose
directions: In 12 ounce glass, mix Ocean Spray cranberry juice cocktail, Bacardi silver or amber rum, lemon juice and grenadine.
Add ice. Garnish with lemon wedge.
Makes 1 serving.

title: toffee-nut candy
directions: Butter a square pan, 9 x 9-inch.
Sread pecans in it.
Heat sugar and butter to boiling, stirring all the time.
Boil over medium heat for 7 minutes.
Spread over nuts in pan.
Place chocolate broken in pieces over hot mixture so chocolate will melt. Cut into squares.
Chill until firm.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and press into oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
While baking, beat 4 eggs.
Add 2 cups sugar, 4 tablespoons flour and 5 tablespoons lemon juice.
Pour onto hot crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sift confectioners sugar on top when done.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: *cheese and mushroom triangles
directions: Combine cheeses and add eggs.
Cut filo in 2-inch strips. Stack and keep covered with damp towel.
Take one strip and brush with butter.
Place another strip on top and brush with butter. Place a rounded teaspoonful of filling on end of strip.
Fold one corner to opposite side to form a triangle.
Continue folding, keeping triangular shape.
Brush top with melted butter.
Place triangles on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
(Freezes well.)

title: mock chicken pie
directions: Melt butter; add flour and cook 2 minutes.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add all other ingredients. Put in buttered baking dish and cover with baking powder biscuit dough.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bird nest cookies
directions: Combine in bowl cereal and coconut.
Bring just to boil while stirring constantly the corn syrup, peanut butter, brown sugar and vanilla.
Remove from heat and stir in the cereal and coconut mixture.
Let cool and then shape into bird's nests.
Put jelly beans in the bird's nests for eggs.
Kids really love this.

title: dumplings for meat stew
directions: Make
stew
and have it cooked thoroughly.
Towards the end of cooking (last 15 minutes or so), mix dumpling ingredients
in a small bowl.
Stir well and drop by spoonful on top of boiling stew.
Cover
tightly
and	cook
about 12 minutes. Turn dumplings
over and cook a few more minutes.
Let simmer if you wish but turn the stew down to a slow cook from now on.

title: meal pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350° or until nicely brown.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Use canned or fresh corn.
Beat eggs; add milk, cream, butter and seasoning to corn.
Put into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until firm and browned on top, about 1 hour.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix cake mix as instructed on the box, except add pudding mix.
Mix well.
Pour this over the top of the melted oleo.
Add peaches over cake batter.
Sprinkle with sugar, then the juice and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: joyce's sugar cookies
directions: Mix all of this together. Place in refrigerator for about 1 hour. (It makes it easier to cut out cookies.) Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mantooke's hermits
directions: Place the first 3 ingredients in a 2-cup measure.
Mix together all ingredients.
Grease a large shallow baking sheet with Mazola.
Spread mixture in the sheet.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cut into rectangles.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: japanese fried rice
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat the mixture thoroughly.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.
Fun to eat with chopsticks.

title: sugar coated pecans
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients until soft stage.
Drop in cold water, turn into ball-candy.
Take off heat.
Throw in pecans.
Drop on wax paper.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Pour all ingredients into a large bowl. Mix until smooth and creamy (10 minutes). Spray three 9 inch round cake pans with cooking spray. Divide cake mix between all three pans. Bake at 325 for approximately 15-20 minutes or until done.

title: gram doris' baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and lay bacon on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: tuna pat
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Pack into a well-oiled 4-cup mold.
Chill at least 3 hours or overnight.
Unmold onto a serving plate and garnish with parsley.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 1 four-cup mold.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water.
Add sherbet.
Refrigerate until the mixture thickens.
Then add whipped cream and remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until mixture thickens.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until soft. Add sugar and salt; toss well.
Cook down slightly until golden brown. Add hot bouillon and bring to a boil.
Add sherry.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon into soup crocks. Add slice of bread and top with cheese. Broil until cheese is brown.

title: remoulade sauce for two
directions: Mix all the above ingredients together, except shrimp and lettuce.
Place shrimp over lettuce, pour sauce over all.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix with electric beaters until well blended.
Sift together next 3 ingredients and add with first mixture.
Blend well.
Add poppy seed and vanilla and beat until smooth.
Turn into greased pans (2 large or 3 small) and bake until brown at 350°, about 60 to 65 minutes.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Heat oven to 375.
Mix brown sugar, shortening, egg and molasses.
Mix in remaining ingredients except granulated sugar. Shape dough by rounded spoons into balls.
Dip tops of balls into granulated sugar.
Place balls, sugar side up, 3 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes.
Let set briefly on cookie sheet before removing to wire rack.
For crispier cookies increase baking time to 10-12 minutes.
Freeze well.

title: strawberry balls
directions: Mix 2 boxes jello, Eagle Brand milk, coconut and pecans. Place in refrigerator and chill. Shape into balls and roll in remaining box of jello.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: shrimp batter
directions: Beat egg well. Add sugar and salt. Add oil. Gradually beat in flour. Beat until smooth. Dip shrimp into batter to coat well. Drop shrimp in hot oil. Brown on both sides. DO NOT overcook!!! Makes enough for approximately 2 pounds shrimp.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil onion, sugar, salt and squash until soft.
Drain and add rest of ingredients.
Save enough crumbs for top.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Place in pan of water and bake for 1 hour.

title: country fried steak
directions: Mix together flour, salt and pepper.
Cut steak into 4 pieces. Coat with flour mixture.
Dip steak in beaten egg or Egg Beaters, then back in flour.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Brown on both sides.
Add water and onion; cover and simmer 1 hour. Drain excess fat.

title: macaroni-beef casserole
directions: Mix ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
Cook and drain off excess.
Pour beef into large bowl.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix with butter, soup and 1 cup water.
Pour over ground beef mixture. Top with Cheddar cheese and let melt in oven.

title: gail's potato wedges
directions: Scrub and quarter potatoes.
Mix all other ingredients in a large shaker bag.
Melt 1 stick of margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan. Shake potatoes in mixture and place in pan in oven.
Bake at 350° to 400° about 45 minutes.
Turn once.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Pierce potatoes with fork.
Microwave on full power for 10 to 13 minutes or until tender, turning once halfway through cooking.
Wrap in clean kitchen towel to keep warm.

title: broccoli with stuffing
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Arrange broccoli in lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs and next three ingredients; spread over cheese.
Combine stuffing mix and margarine; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for thirty minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: cold german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs.
Fry bacon.
Stir hot bacon grease into the chopped onions and celery.
Mix salad dressing, mayonnaise and sugar.
Blend bacon grease mixture and salad dressing mixture.
Mix in the potatoes.
Cut up 7 of the 8 eggs. Mix them in.
This has to be last so the eggs are not crushed too bad.
With the last egg, slice and decorate.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley; serve.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: scuffy brownie cake(makes 12 servings; prep time: 20 minutes)
directions: Mix together the first 4 dry ingredients.
Bring to a boil the water, 4 tablespoons cocoa and 2 sticks butter.
ADD to the dry mixture.
ADD the 1/2 cup buttermilk, eggs and vanilla to the mixture.
Pour into a jelly roll pan and bake for 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken almondine
directions: Cook chicken until tender (not soft).
Remove from bone and cut into fairly large pieces. Cook celery in broth till crisp tender. Cook rice following directions of package
using chicken broth for liquid.
Mix all ingredients but reserve some of the almonds to sprinkle on top.
Bake 45 minutes in 350 degrees oven. Too moist - cook longer.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Puncture tenderloin every inch on top and insert sliver of garlic.
Place in roasting pan and cook for 3/4 to 1 hour at 325°, or until meat thermometer reaches 160° to 170°.
About 20 minutes before roast is done, cut onion and bell pepper into slices and add to pan.
Save juices for gravy.

title: greek hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients except onions.
Form into hamburger patties and fry.
In another pan, melt butter and fry onions until soft.
Serve hamburgers on buns.
Top with fried onions, lettuce and tomato.

title: sauerkraut salad(this salad goes great with polish sausage.)
directions: Mix the vegetables together in a large bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients to the vegetables, and mix well.
Cover and chill for 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pistachio fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in 9 x 9-inch dish. Sprinkle top with nuts and refrigerate.

title: grace's easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in 4 quarts water (salt and pepper) in Dutch oven until falling off of bones.
Debone and deskin chicken (cook broth down to about 2 quarts).
Add butter and margarine to hot broth.

title: best brownies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening (or margarine). Add eggs and mix well. Stir in cocoa, flour, salt, vanilla and nuts.

title: hot tamales
directions: You will need parchment paper.

title: hot water corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal and salt.
Add enough boiling water to cook and moisten the corn meal.
The mixture should be the consistency of mashed potatoes.
You may add more water, if you need too.

title: walnut bark
directions: Place saltines on foil lined cookie tray. Melt butter and brown sugar and then pour this mixture over the crackers. Bake in preheated 400° oven about 5 minutes or until bubbling. Remove and sprinkle with chocolate chips, letting them melt, then spread with back of spoon. Add walnuts and press in slightly. Refrigerate for an hour or so; then either break or cut into pieces.

title: crumb cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add flour.
Mix well and reserve 1 cup of mixture.
Add rest of ingredients to crumb mixture.
Beat well.
Put in shallow pan.
Sprinkle top with cup of crumbs and bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine, sugar, eggs, flour, baking soda and salt.
Mash bananas and add to mixture.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses (Cheddar first) in food processor until smooth.
Roll into a ball using wax paper; chop nuts and pour over ball.
Continue rolling on wax paper until ball is coated with nuts.
Other ingredients may be added if desired during processing.

title: fig pockets
directions: Cover figs with water and cook until soft; drain.
Cut off stems and buds, then grind to a pulp.
Add vanilla, sugar, lemon juice and nuts.
Spoon mixture onto crescent rolls and fold corners to make an envelope shape.
Bake according to roll package directions.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tiny raisin-apple loaves
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until done.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk, then fold in Cool Whip. Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers, then spread with half of the pudding mixture. Add another layer of graham crackers and the rest of the pudding mixture. Add another layer of graham crackers. Top with the icing. Better if made about 8 hours ahead.

title: laura sutton's raisin nut cookies
directions: Cream
sugar
and
Crisco
together.
Gradually
add in eggs. Mix thoroughly and
then add cinnamon.
Pour one cup of flour over raisins and nuts.
Gradually pour 2 cups flour into mixture.
Add water and
after
thoroughly mixed, pour in nuts and raisins. Bake approximately 12 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed prunes
directions: Open hole in prune.
Stuff with cream cheese, then insert 1 pecan half in center of each.

title: potato salad
directions: Mash potatoes with potato masher.
Combine all ingredients. Stir well and pour into salad dish.

title: tasty turkey loaf
directions: Place all ingredients in large mixing bowl and mix with hands. Put mixture into loaf pan, sprayed with low-calorie spray.
Make sure mixture is pressed into corners and along sides.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let loaf stand 15 minutes before slicing.
Makes 6 servings.

title: heavenly potato topping
directions: Heat oil in a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add peas.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add water chestnuts, garlic, ginger, soy sauce and hot pepper sauce.
Cook 2 minutes, or until peas are crisp-tender.
Garnish with cilantro sprigs.
Serve immediately. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: butter crackers
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; boil for 2 minutes.
Place Club crackers on cookie sheet.
Place chopped pecans on crackers. Pour the oleo-butter-sugar mixture over crackers.
Bake for 8 minutes at 350°.

title: fantastic microwave fudge
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and margarine.
Cook on High in microwave for 2 minutes.
Remove, stir and add vanilla and nuts.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Freeze cranberries, then grind or chip in blender.
Mix sugar and frozen cranberries and let stand several hours.
Drain.
Drain crushed pineapple and combine Cool Whip, pineapple, grapes, nuts and cranberries.
Refrigerate.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except cocktail sauce.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with cocktail sauce; spread over top.
Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate or peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk; bring to a rolling boil. Cook rapidly 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly. Mixture will scorch easily.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate morsels.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool; cut in squares.

title: tea time tassies
directions: Soften butter and cream cheese. Blend together.
Add flour. Chill 1
hour.

title: stuffed cornish hens
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Sprinkle hens with salt, pepper, and garlic powder inside and out. In a frying pan, saute bacon until soft. Add onions, green peppers, and garlic and cook over medium heat until soft, and until bacon is done. Remove with slotted spoon to a large mixing bowl. Add rice, mushrooms, and green onions and toss to mix well. Stuff into hens. Place 3 pats of butter on each hen and wrap with aluminum foil. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes; open foil and bake 15 more minutes to brown hens.

title: green pepper and eggs
directions: In soup bowl, mix eggs with onion powder, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Let set.

title: tea cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients except flour.
Alternate flour with a mixture of other ingredients until a thick dough is formed.
Roll out dough on a cookie board to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into squares. Place on a cookie sheet that is ungreased.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until browned.
Frost or serve plain.
Makes about 7 dozen large tea cakes.
Recipe may be halved, if desired.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate several hours.
Good with raw vegetables.

title: strawberry cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Stir occasionally until thawed.
Add pineapple and pour half of the salad into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Spread evenly with sour cream.
Pour remaining jello atop and chill firm.

title: quick and easy pizza snack
directions: Split muffins in half.
Top with salsa.
You can add browned hamburger, sausage, ham, pepperoni, peppers or mushrooms if you like.
Top with cheese.
Microwave until cheese melts.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, cheese and pineapple.
Put in dish. Sprinkle crackers on top.
Pour butter over mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cornmeal rolls
directions: Mix cornmeal, sugar, salt, shortening and milk in medium pan until thick (like cooked cereal).
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast, which has been dissolved in lukewarm water, then eggs.
Beat thoroughly.
Add flour to form soft dough.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix grated potatoes and milk.
Drain milk and add egg, flour and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto well-greased pan.
Brown on both sides.

title: apple-almond buttermilk pancakes
directions: Whip egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Set aside.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Spread a thin layer on flat tortilla. Roll tortilla tightly and wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours.
