Cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: chicken in pastry
directions: Skin and bone chicken.
Saute in butter, garlic salt and tarragon.
Whip the cream cheese with some chopped chives and parsley.
Roll out patty shells, one at a time, between waxed paper.
Place layer of cream cheese mixture on pastry.
Put chicken on top and wrap pastry around it all.
Bake, folded side down, on greased pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 425°.
You can brush with beaten egg, milk or melted butter so it will brown nicely.
Serves 6.

title: aunt amy's cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder, and salt set aside. Cream shortening and sugars, until light and fluffy. Stir in egg, vanilla, Grape-Nut Flakes and oatmeal.

Stir together well. Stir in flour mixture. Arrange by teaspoons on buttered cookie sheet. Flatten with a knife or fork dipped in cold water. For very delicate cookies, flatten until almost paper-thin.

title: beans, beans, beans!
directions: Brown bacon, meat and onion; drain and pat well.
Add catsup and remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Great for dinners, picnics, etc.
Kids and adults both love this!

title: banana and pineapple cheese pie
directions: Mix
cream cheese, large Cool Whip and sugar.
Spread in pie shell.
Cover with small Cool Whip.
Arrange banana slices and pineapple slices and pecans on top.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: southern pralines
directions: Combine sugar, cream, butter and salt in a heavy saucepan. Cook, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes.
Add nuts.
Stir until mixture coats a spoon.
Drop on buttered wax paper.
Makes 30 to 35 pralines.

title: chess cookies
directions: Grease sheet pan.
Mix cake mix, 1 egg and margarine.
Press evenly into pan.

title: mom's fast chili
directions: In a large saucepan, cook beef and onion over medium-high heat, stirring often to break up meat, until lightly browned, 5 to 10 minutes. Drain off fat. Stir in all remaining ingredients. Heat to boiling; reduce heat to medium-low and simmer, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes. Serve topped with shredded cheese, onion and light sour cream.

title: veal forestier
directions: With meat mallet, pound cutlets to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut cutlets into 3 x 2-inch pieces.
On wax paper, coat cutlets lightly with flour.

In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot butter or margarine, cook meat, a few pieces at a time, until lightly browned on both sides, removing pieces as they brown and adding more butter or margarine if necessary.
Add mushrooms, vermouth, water, salt and pepper to skillet.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes, or until mushrooms are tender.
Return meat to skillet; heat through. Makes 4 servings.

title: sesame chicken
directions: In a non-stick skillet - over medium heat, add sesame seeds and stir constantly for 1-2 minutes until toasted.
Remove.
Beat chicken breasts thin between saran wrap until 1/4 inch thick.
Coat skillet with cooking spray and place over medium heat until hot, add chicken and cook 3 minutes on each side until brown.
Combine sesame seeds, syrup, soy sauce, and ginger.
Pour over chicken and cook for 1 more minute, turning chicken to coat with sauce.
Serve with rice and broccoli and mushroom stir-fry.

title: lazy cake
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Make hole in mixture and add the remaining ingredients; mix as you would cornbread.
Do not beat!
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes (about).

title: sauce mornay
directions: In small,
heavy saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour. Add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until it boils.
Lower flame. Add
cheese
and
cook,
stirring
constantly,
for
5 minutes or until smooth and well blended.

title: tuna casserolegroves, texas
directions: Cook macaroni.
Mix Cream of Mushroom soup, cheese, tuna, pimento and macaroni.

title: crab apples
directions: Cut blossoms off apples and wash.
Boil apples in clear water until apples crack. (If apples don't split, don't overcook.)

title: debbie's eggs
directions: Cube bread and put in a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex pan.
(I use two small pans and freeze one.)
Melt cheese, butter and margarine. Pour over bread crumbs.
Mix eggs and milk.
Pour over mixture. Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake in a 300° oven for one hour.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
Shape into balls.
Put in refrigerator until firm.
Mix remaining ingredients and roll balls in mixture, then in coconut.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Combine sugar, buttermilk, baking soda and corn syrup in a large saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil to soft boil stage (234° to 238°).
Just before removing from heat, add butter and vanilla. Remove from heat and stir in pecans.
Beat until mixture loses its gloss and holds its shape.
Drop in mounds on wax paper and let cool.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: oregano meatballs
directions: Mix bread, milk, onion and salt.
Whip well.
Add meat and mix well.
Make into small balls.
Brown in butter.
Remove meatballs; drain grease.
Add ketchup, oregano and sherry (bouillon).
Return meatballs and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over hot rice or noodles.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Place 1/3 cup sugar, shortening and salt in large bowl.
Pour boiling water over, dissolving the shortening.
When cooled to lukewarm, sprinkle in yeast.
When yeast dissolves, add eggs and mix well.
Add flour.
Stir lightly until flour is moistened. Cover with clean, dry cloth.
Place in warm place.
I have oven hot and set bowl on top of stove.
Let rise for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together. Blend in eggs; beat well. Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder together. Add to mixture. Add pineapple and vanilla. If batter is stiff, add a little of juice. Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. When cool, add icing to each cookie.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Test for doneness by inserting cake tester or case knife, should come out clean and dry.

title: old fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Butter a 2-quart casserole.
Set aside.
Bring water to a rapid boil in a heavy 4-quart saucepan.
Add 1 teaspoon of salt and oil.
Gradually add macaroni, being sure water continues to boil.
Cook macaroni, uncovered, until tender, but firm.
Stir occasionally.
Drain.
Place in prepared casserole.

title: goulash gravy
directions: Brown ground chuck with onion and green pepper; drain.
Return to kettle and add tomatoes, 1 1/2 cans water, salt, pepper and dry beef broth.
Simmer 30 minutes; add more water if needed.
Thicken with flour and water to make as thick as you like.
Serve over noodles, rice or potatoes.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Mix together all ingredients except the chicken.
Spray baking pan with nonstick cooking
spray.
Place chicken in pan, skin side up.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°. Baste every 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine all except cheese and potato chips.
Toss lightly and put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spread chips and cheese on top. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes until heated through and browned.
Garnish with paprika and parsley.

title: eggnog
directions: Blend bourbon and sugar. Let stand overnight, stirring occasionally. Beat egg yolks until light and fluffy. Combine egg yolks and bourbon mixture, stirring constantly. Allow eggs and bourbon to stand 2 1/2 hours. Whip cream until stiff and gently fold into bourbon mixture. Chill in refrigerator and serve in chilled cups. Serves 30.

title: mom's (tookie) lasagna
directions: Brown beef in a 3-quart saucepan; drain excess fat.
Add sauce and water.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients, except lasagna, for filling.

title: buttered carrots
directions: Boil carrots in salted water about 15 minutes.
Drain.
Add butter and onion; stir over low fire 5 minutes (until onions are tender).

title: delicious cheese ball
directions: Mix well and shape.
Serve immediately or refrigerate to serve later.

title: microwave chocolate fudge
directions: Put butter, milk and chips in microwave on 50% power until melted.
Stir a couple of times.
Add nuts.
Pour into dish. Refrigerate until hard.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all together except oil.
Fry in the oil.

title: dill pickles
directions: I usually double this brine.
Rinse jars in hot water, then pack with dill, a couple cloves of garlic and clean pickles. Cover with hot brine within 1/4-inch of tops that are kept in hot water.
Tighten down but not real tight.
Put in canner of very hot or slightly boiling water.
Have water only to curve of jar. After the water begins boiling again, boil only 5 minutes.
Remove from canner.
Tighten down lids.
Set them on a towel and cover them with a towel.
Leave overnight.
Remove screw tops and store.

title: ground beef noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat with seasoning salt, garlic and onion powder and black pepper.
Drain off excess fat from hamburger meat.
Stir in tomato sauce and cream-style corn.
Add approximately 1 cup of water.
Mix well.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Boil noodles until tender.
Put boiled noodles in bottom of casserole dish or pan. Pour ground beef mixture on top.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top of ground beef mixture.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: coconut-black walnut pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients; add to sugar mixture.
Alternate with buttermilk; beat well.
Stir in nuts, coconut and coconut extract.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes (some ovens vary).
Pour hot coconut syrup over hot cake.
Allow to remain in pan at least 4 hours or overnight.
Run knife around sides and middle of pan.
Remove from pan.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients, including sugar, into mixing bowl.
Make a well in dry ingredients and add all remaining ingredients.
Mix together until smooth.
Apportion batter into 3 conventional bread loaf pans that have been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.
Cool slightly in pans, then turn onto racks to finish cooling.
Wrap in foil or plastic and store in refrigerator or freeze, if desired.
Slice thin and spread with butter.
Serve open-faced or as small sandwich.
Bread should be made at least 1 day before using.
Makes 3 loaves.
Chopped pecans may be added.
Can substitute shredded zucchini in place of the pumpkin.

title: baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken in beaten eggs.
Make mixture of flour, lemon pepper and garlic. Dip chicken in mixture.
Put chicken in glass casserole dish.
Put pat of butter on each piece.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet and top with chopped nuts or coconut.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ten day rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water for 5 minutes.
Pour boiling water over crisco, sugar, salt.
Blend and cool.
Add eggs.
Stir yeast into mixture.
Add flour.
Blend well.
Cover and place in refrigerator 5 hours.
Looks runny.

title: marla's corn pudding
directions: Mix together.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: saturday night supper
directions: In a skillet, brown chops evenly in oil, about 10 minutes on each side.
Drain chops on paper towels.
Pour beans into a 2 quart casserole and place chops on top of beans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
In a small bowl, combine jelly and water.
Baste chops with this mixture and arrange apple slices on top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Return to oven and continue baking for another 15 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Add ingredients in order in large bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 14 dozen.

title: lemon soda
directions: In a glass, put seltzer water, lemonade Kool-Aid mix and sugar.
Stir.
Add ice if desired.
Relax, sip and enjoy.

title: peach pie alaska
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls.
Stir until melted and smooth.
Blend in whipped topping and fruit.
Chill, if necessary, until mixture will mound. Spoon into crust.
Chill about 3 hours, or freeze until firm. Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Combine butter, sugar and pretzels.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese with sugar. Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Chill.
Make jello; add fruit.
Cool.
Pour on top of cream layer.
Chill until set.

title: chili con queso that will knock your socks off!
directions: Heat together in large crock-pot.

title: mashed potato candy
directions: Combine mashed potatoes, vanilla or almond extract, powdered sugar and coconut; mix well.
Chill overnight.
Shape into balls. Chill again.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler. Dip candy in chocolate.
Place on waxed paper to set.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Place flank steak in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch glass dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Remove meat, discarding marinade.
Grill until meat reaches desired doneness, about 4 minutes per side for medium and 5 minutes per side for medium well.
Slice into thin strips across the grain to serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oven-bake or grilled chuck roast
directions: Sprinkle tenderizer on both sides of roast.
Bake like a steak in oven at about 350°.
Spread each side with butter and garlic sauce once or twice, using all the butter and garlic sauce.
Bake to desired doneness.
Ten minutes before done, spread roast with mushrooms.

title: pastitsio
directions: Cook macaroni, drain.
Combine macaroni, 1 egg, 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese and the 1/4 cup milk.
Set aside.
Brown meat and onion in skillet; drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, cinnamon, nutmeg, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper; set aside.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add the 1 1/2 cups milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened. Remove from heat.
Stir about half of the hot mixture into beaten egg.
Return to remaining hot mixture.
Stir in 1/4 cup cheese. Place half macaroni mixture in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Spoon the meat mixture on top, add the remaining macaroni mixture. Spread the sauce over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes.

title: wedding
directions: Boil in pinch of soda and water for about 1 hour.
Rubber will come up again.

title: grandma guldenstein's molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order; roll out and cut with any shape cookie cutter.
Bake at 360° for about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: philly pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese.
Add sugar and cream again. Add vanilla and eggs; mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in a wax paper-lined loaf pan (1 1/2 recipes fill a tube pan).
Also makes a great Easter lamb!

title: baked alaska
directions: Cut fruit and ice cream into convenient pieces.
Place in freezer to re-freeze. Prepare meringue as follows:
Beat whites, slightly. Add salt and vanilla. Continue beating until very stiff. Add sugar, a tablespoon at a time, and beat only until sugar is well blended.
Place shortcakes on cookie sheet.
Place frozen fruit in center, the ice cream on top. Cover generously with meringue.
Bake at 450° for 4 to 5 minutes. Watch them carefully.

title: garbage, ugly dig chilies rellenos dig
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Drain if needed.
Serve with plain Doritos.

title: plum or peach custard dessert
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Sift flour, salt, cinnamon and baking powder.
Blend into creamed mixture until crumbly.
Measure out about 1/3 of mixture and press remaining mixture evenly into bottom and about 1 inch up sides of ungreased 9-inch pie pan. Arrange plums or peaches in shell.
Sprinkle with saved mixture. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: snow pudding
directions: Soak gelatine in milk for 5 minutes.
Cook over low flame until gelatine is dissolved, then add sugar.
Remove from heat and slowly add beaten egg yolks.
Return to heat until you notice a slight thickening similar to cream.
Remove from heat and stir in salt and vanilla.
Add 3 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Stir well and refrigerate.
The pudding will separate into a layer of custard with a frothy (snowy) layer on top.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Dredge next 4 ingredients in flour mixture.
Cream together butter, sugar and eggs.
Combine buttermilk and soda.
Add buttermilk and soda to butter, egg and sugar mixture, alternating with flour.
Add candy mixture, folding in well.
Bake at 275° to 300° for 1 3/4 to 2 hours.

title: blintz souffle
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart casserole and place blintzes in one layer.
Mix remaining ingredients well and pour over blintzes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
You may use 2 packages of the same flavor of blintzes, or you can mix them.

title: marshside toll house pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour and sugars.
Add cooled butter and beat for 3 minutes.
Add chocolate bits and nuts. Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken with artichokes(serve with rice.)
directions: Sprinkle chicken with paprika, salt, pepper and parsley.
Melt butter in a large skillet. Add olive oil to heat.
When foam subsides, brown chicken on both sides.
Remove chicken pieces and place in large serving casserole with airtight fitting lid. Add artichokes, cutting pieces if necessary.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°f. 230°c. gas mark 8. Stir together the flour, baking powder and salt, then cut in the butter until the mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs.
Stir in just enough milk so the dough comes together into a ball leaving the sides of the bowl clean. Too much will make the dough sticky, not enough will make the biscuits dry.
Turn the dough onto a lightly floured surface and knead slightly to make the dough nice and smooth.
Roll out to 1/2 thick, cut with a floured biscuit cutter.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet about 1 inch apart.
Bake for 10-12 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from the cookie sheet.
Makes about 10-12 biscuits.

title: easy peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour;
sprinkle over peaches.
Mix carefully
to
avoid tearing peaches.
Pour into deep dish pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Top with regular pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at	450°.
Turn
oven
down
to 350° and bake about 40 minutes longer.

title: applesauce bars
directions: Mix flour with soda and spices.
Cream margarine with white sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well. Stir in flour mixture.
Add applesauce, nuts and raisins and stir until blended.
Pour into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes or until done.
Cool, then cut. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Flatten rolls in an 11 x 14-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake as directed on can; let cool completely.
Mix together until smooth. Spread mayonnaise on top.
Top with fresh vegetables.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.

title: healthy lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook lasagna noodles as directed on package, omitting oil.
Combine cottage cheese, egg whites, Parmesan cheese, pepper and parsley flakes in a separate bowl.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, add drained corn, onion, potatoes, milk, water and carrots.
Heat, then add bouillon cube.
Simmer on medium heat until potatoes are tender.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Thicken, if desired, with a roux (equal amounts of melted butter and flour).

title: angel food dream cake
directions: Bring to a rolling boil in a saucepan sugar, water, pineapple and Jell-O.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes and chill until firm.
Whip heavy cream and fold in Jell-O mixture.
Frost cake, filling hole. Return to refrigerator and chill until serving.
Can be frozen.

title: clara's hot homemade mayonnaise
directions: In blender, beat egg yolk, then add vinegar. Beat.

Add mustard, seasoned salt and red pepper and mix well. Drop oil, one teaspoon at a time, into egg mixture, beating constantly, until 1/4 cup oil is used. Drizzle oil in slowly, beating constantly, until rest of oil is blended in.
When mixture is thickened, add the lemon juice, a little at a time, until well blended. Keep stored in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, flour, baking powder, soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, oil, water, pumpkin and eggs.
(I usually mix dry ingredients and make a little pond in middle and add remainder ingredients.)
Makes 1 loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water for 10 to 15 minutes. Drain, reserving 1 cup of cooking liquid.
Place potatoes in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Melt butter or margarine.
Remove 1 tablespoon butter; toss with bread crumbs, paprika and thyme and set crumbs aside.
Into remaining butter, blend flour, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add reserved cooking liquid and milk or cream. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in ham and cheese. Cook until cheese is melted.
Pour sauce over potatoes and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer and put in crust. Refrigerate.

title: tropical punch
directions: Use a tall glass.
Pour in lime juice, pineapple juice and ice cubes.
Fill with Slice or Sprite soda.
Stir.
Garnish with cherry or pineapple chunks.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix in a sauce pan the sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Heat and stir to full boil.
Remove from heat and cool 1 minute.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, Miracle Whip and chili powder.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer meat mixture, then 1/2 of crushed chips and 1/2 of cheese.
Make another layer. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: reese's peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Prepare cookie mix as directed on package.
Fill mini-muffin cups one-half full of cookie mix.
Press unwrapped peanut butter cup in center of cookie mix.
Bake in center of oven at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Let cool before removing from muffin tin. Yield: 36 cookies.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin, oil, water and rum.
Combine with dry ingredients, mixing well.
Fold in pecans and raisins.
Bake in two loaf pans for 45 to 60 minutes at 325°.
Bread pulls away from side of pan when done and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Place popcorn in large heatproof bowl in oven.
Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil over medium heat for 5 minutes; do not stir. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour over hot popcorn, stirring until coated.
Mix in nuts.
Pour into greased 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour until golden brown, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and break into pieces. Store in airtight container.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add sugar and dissolve.
Add cold water to Jell-O mixture.
Then add pineapple, Mandarin oranges and coconut.
Put in refrigerator until partly jelled. Then add Cool Whip; mix well.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat and onion together. Add tomatoes, sauce, paste and all other ingredients except mushrooms. Let simmer for about 1 hour. Near end of cooking time, add mushrooms. Makes enough sauce for about 1/2 pound of cooked spaghetti.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt morsels and peanut butter in microwave for 3 minutes. Stir after each minute until smooth.
Pour over noodles; stir until well covered.
Drop onto wax paper, 1 to 2 teaspoons in size.
Will harden in about 15 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on; let cool.
Grate or chop coarsely.
Set aside.
Melt butter over low heat.
Remove from heat and add cheese, sour cream and onion flakes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in potatoes and bake in a buttered casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: beefburger specials
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into 4 large (1/2-inch thick) or 8 small (1/4-inch thick) patties.
Broil on pan 3-inches below source of heat, about 6 minutes on each side for larger patties, 4 minutes for smaller ones.

title: chicken vegetable
directions: Bring chicken broth to boil. Add potato, carrot, celery, green beans and onion. Boil 12 minutes. Add rest of ingredients. Simmer 10 minutes.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crush Oreo cookies with rolling pin.
Place 1/2 crumb mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar until smooth.
Set aside.
In another bowl, mix pudding and milk.
Blend the 2 mixtures together.
Spread over cookie crumbs.
Sprinkle remainder of crumbs on top.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Put lettuce in large glass bowl.
Add remaining vegetables in layers in the order given.
Spread mayonnaise on top.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Add cheese and finally bacon.
Cover with plastic wrap for 8 to 24 hours.
Do not stir or season.

title: tex-mex tortilla soup
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch cubes; set aside.
In large saucepan, combine water, beef and chicken broth, undrained tomatoes, onion and bell pepper; bring to a boil.

Add chicken and reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Add corn, chili powder, cumin and pepper. Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes more. To serve, place crushed tortilla chips in each bowl and ladle soup over them. Sprinkle with cheese and place avocado pieces on top. Makes 6 servings.

title: seafood cheese fondue
directions: Rub pot with garlic.
Heat soup in pot and beat until smooth. Slowly add milk and beat again.
Add cheese slowly, stirring as it melts.
Sprinkle with pepper and paprika and place over burner. Dunk the seafood and bread using fondue forks.

title: indian chow-chow
directions: Put spices in 2 bags.
Mix remaining ingredients with 1 tablespoon salt and boil together until apples are done.
Put in jars and seal.

title: angie's easy lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown meat and onion. Drain. Add spaghetti sauce and water. Simmer 10 minutes. In a large bowl, stir together Ricotta cheese, half of Mozzarella, Monterey Jack and Parmesan cheese. Add eggs, parsley, salt and pepper. Pour about 1 cup of sauce on the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Arrange 3 uncooked pasta pieces lengthwise over sauce. Cover with about 1 cup of sauce. Spread half of the cheese filling over sauce. Repeat layers of lasagne, filling and cheese mixture. Top with remaining layers of lasagne noodles and sauce. Sprinkle with the remaining shredded cheese. Cover with nonstick foil. Bake 45 minutes. Remove foil. Bake an additional 15 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes and cut.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except cream cheese in the top of a double boiler.
Stir and cook until thick.
Let cool.
Whip cream cheese until fluffy and mix thoroughly with other ingredients. Chill.
Use as a dip for fresh pineapple, strawberries or melon balls.

title: hammy corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add soups, water, milk and seasonings.
Stir until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cream flour, margarine and powdered sugar.
Press evenly in bottom of ungreased square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Beat remaining ingredients until light and fluffy.
Pour over hot crust and bake 20 to 25 minutes longer.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix together and freeze in ice cream freezer.
Very delicious. Works well in hand or electric crank.

title: pineapple cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and vanilla, mixing well.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Place in a cold oven.
Set temperature at 325° and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool 15 to 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: hillbilly fried pies
directions: Mix pastry as usual.
Work dough into a firm ball. Divide pastry in half.
On lightly floured surface, roll 1/2 into about 10-inch square. Cut into four 5-inch squares or circles.
Repeat with other half of dough, after filling the first 4.
I like to cook dried fruit until tender, sweeten to taste and use enough water to keep from sticking. Fry in about 1-inch of Crisco on medium heat, turning once.

title: wassail
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bring to boil and serve hot.

title: banana chocolate chip bread
directions: Mash 3 large ripe bananas.
Add to mixture of oil, sugar and eggs.
Add mixture of flour, soda and salt, then add 1 bag mini chocolate chips.
Mix by hand.
Pour in 4 greased mini loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool completely.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and tinfoil.
Store overnight before serving.
Freezes well.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar with broccoli, bacon, sunflower seeds, onion and raisins.
Best to add the bacon and sunflower seeds just before serving.

title: delmonico deviled chicken
directions: Mix butter, mustard, vinegar, salt and paprika.
Rub the mixture over the chicken.
Place chicken in a shallow roasting pan.
Sprinkle evenly with the crumbs and bake for 40 minutes or until done in a 375° oven.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Boil onions and pour juice off.
Mix liquid smoke with onion juice, steak sauce, butter, lemon and Worcestershire; mix well.

title: died and gone to heaven pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and place in crust.
Serve cold.

title: rhubarb squares(rhubarb dream bars)
directions: Mix the flour, powdered sugar and margarine until crumbly. Put in jelly roll pan; bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat well the eggs, flour and sugar, then fold in the rhubarb.
Put on top of hot crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Combine
beef,	salt, pepper, bread crumbs, onion and 1 can tomato
sauce;
mix
well.	Place
equal portions of meat mixture in center of each cabbage leaf.
Fold ends over, roll up
and fasten
with
toothpicks.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour	over cabbage
rolls.
Cover;
cook over low heat for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini and mushroom frittata
directions: Saute the zucchini, mushrooms, onions, parsley and garlic in olive oil.
Mix the eggs, cheese, basil, salt and pepper together and combine with the zucchini mixture.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until set.

title: layered pasta ricotta pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Break vermicelli into thirds; cook according to package directions.
Drain.
Meanwhile, in large skillet, cook onion and garlic in oil until tender; remove from heat.
Add cooked vermicelli, 1/2 cup Romano cheese and 1 egg; mix well.
Press into well-greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine 2 egg yolks, Ricotta cheese, spinach, salt and remaining 1/2 cup Romano cheese.
Spread over pasta layer.
In small mixer bowl, beat 2 egg whites until stiff, but not dry; fold into 1 1/2 cups pasta sauce.
Pour over spinach mixture.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until set; let stand 10 minutes.
Heat remaining pasta sauce; serve with pie.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Sprinkle both sides of pork chops with salt and pepper.
Dip pork chops into beaten eggs, roll in cracker meal.
Place pork chops in skillet in small amount of fat.
Cook over medium heat, turning to brown both sides.
Remove from skillet.
Place in roasting pan.
Cover top of roasting pan with wax paper.
Place lid over paper.
Trim off excess paper from around the lid.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken with asparagus sauce
directions: Dip chicken into egg; coat with bread crumbs.
In skillet over medium-low heat, in hot oil, cook chicken 15 minutes or until browned on both sides and not pink inside.
Remove and keep warm. In same skillet over low heat, combine soup, milk and water.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Spoon mixture over chicken and serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: white trash or puppy chow
directions: Mix cereal, peanuts and raisins together.
Melt butter and add chocolate chips and peanut butter, stir well.
Mix well with cereal mixture until coated.
Using a double brown paper bag, layer mix and confectioners sugar. Shake.
Makes 5 1/2 quarts.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix broccoli and rice after cooked. Mix cream of mushroom soup, Cheez Whiz and cream cheese; heat slightly. Add to broccoli and rice. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Stir in cream of celery soup and water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: southern banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix, egg yolks and milk in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture just comes to boil.
Remove from heat.
Cover surface of hot pudding with waxed paper or plastic wrap and cool.
Beat cooled pudding until smooth.

title: garden tenderloin rolls
directions: In a large saucepan, combine asparagus, carrots and 3/4 cup water.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, then simmer, covered, for 4 to 6 minutes, just until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Cut the pork into 8 pieces.
Place each piece between 2 pieces of clear plastic wrap.
Pound into a 4 to 5-inch circle.
Sprinkle with pepper. Divide asparagus and carrots evenly among the 8 pieces of meat. Roll up jelly roll style.
Place seam side down, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake, covered, in a 375° oven for 15 minutes. Uncover and bake 5 to 10 minutes more or until meat is no longer pink.

title: basic multigrain pancakes
directions: After Step
you can add a variety of fruits to these pancakes (cranberries, blueberries, raisins, apples, pears and bananas).
Add
some
cinnamon
to	recipe	or
sprinkle
some cinnamon-sugar on top before the pancake cooks.
Your imagination is your only limitation.

title: cheesy rice-beef bake
directions: Cook beef, drain and set aside.
Brown uncooked rice in butter in a large skillet. Stir in water, carrots or corn, beef bouillon, parsley, onion, salt and basil. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in browned beef.
Put in a 1 1/2 quart casserole. Cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: snack pretzels
directions: Mix spices, dressing mix and oil together.
Pour over pretzels.
Mix.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes, stirring often.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix milk,
egg	yolks
and lime juice together.
Beat 1 egg white
stiff.
Fold into the mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell. Beat
egg whites.
Gradually add sugar and cream of tartar. Spread over filling, forming peaks.
Bake until brown at 350°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill for 2 hours before serving. Serve with crackers or chips.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spray pans with Pam.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
I usually add extra raisins.
Bake at 400°.
(Can be stored in refrigerator for 6 weeks.)

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Combine sauce, spices and onions.
Mix together noodles, hamburger or other meat of your choice and sauce.
In large casserole, layer noodles, meat mixture and cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: olives on horseback
directions: Roll large green stuffed olives in a strip of bacon and broil until bacon is crisp.
Serve on toothpicks.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Add pepperoni, mushrooms and pizza sauce.
Heat.
Roll out 1 can of crescent rolls in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour hamburger mixture over top. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over hamburger mixture.
Place the other can of crescent rolls on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until crescent rolls are golden.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish; stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Cook 8 minutes on High in a microwave.
Stir well after 4 minutes.
Stir in margarine and vanilla.
Put in microwave 2 more minutes on High.
Add baking soda and quickly stir until light and foamy.
Pour immediately into a greased baking sheet. Spread thin.
Cool and break into pieces.
Store in a tight container.
Roasted peanuts may be substituted instead of raw, but must be added just before soda.

title: my pound cake
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, flour and flavoring, slowly,
then
beat
at full speed for about 5 minutes. Pour
into
greased
tube
cake pan.
Makes large pound cake.

title: yum-yum bread
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan. Place rolls in pan. Mix brown sugar and pudding. Sprinkle over rolls. Mix sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over rolls.
Sprinkle on nuts. Pour melted butter over it all. Let set overnight to rise. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix with Miracle Whip.

title: mama's macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni and drain.
Heat oven to 350°; melt 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add flour, milk and chicken flavor; simmer until thick.
Add cheese.
Mix.
Spoon into greased casserole. Bake 30 minutes until bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rum cake
directions: Sprinkle pecans in bottom of small greased and floured tube pan.
Put cake mix and pudding into bowl.
Add rum and oil.
Mix well.
Add eggs one at a time; mix well as they are added.
Pour batter over nuts in pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done. Cool in pan for 20 minutes then turn onto plate and top with glaze.

title: sugar-free cherry pie
directions: Mix pudding, Jell-O and juice from cherries. Cook until thick; add cherries. Stir. Pour in pie shell. Top with pie crust or lattice. Be sure to cut slits in top pie crust. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Beat cream cheese, mayonnaise, salt and lemon juice.
Put pepper, carrots and onion in a blender.
Add water.
Blend and drain.
Add to other ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix chicken, broth, soup, eggs and vegetables in long pan.

title: pizza pie
directions: Dissolve yeast in the warm water; add sugar, salt and oil and mix thoroughly.
Add 1/2 of the flour and beat until there are no lumps.
Add remaining flour; knead dough 5 minutes.
Take half of dough and roll out to about 12 inches in diameter.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Leave edges a little thicker.
Repeat with the rest of dough on second cookie sheet.
Let rise 20 to 30 minutes.
Brush tops with salad oil.

title: watergate salad
directions: Fold dry pudding into Cool Whip. Add other ingredients. Stir and refrigerate.

title: microwave ham roll-ups
directions: Microwave cream cheese in a small bowl on High until softened, 10 to 15 seconds.
Stir in Cheddar cheese, green onion and mustard.
Spread cheese mixture on ham slices.
Roll ham from narrow end.
Cut each roll into 4 pieces.
Secure with wooden pick.
Place on paper towel or large dinner plate.
Microwave on High 45 seconds to 1 minute and 30 seconds.

title: krispy fingers
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar, egg and dates.
Cook 10 minutes. Remove from heat; add vanilla, Rice Krispies and nuts.
Stir until cool and roll in fingers.
Roll in coconut.
Store in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: best fruitcake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add 1 1/4 cups flour and the flavorings. Mix well.
Set aside.
Mix 1/2 cup flour with nuts and fruits; stir to well mixed.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter, then pour over nuts and fruit.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Start in cold oven at 250°.
Bake for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift first five ingredients; set aside.
In large bowl, beat eggs; add sugar.
Blend together.
Add pumpkin and oil; blend. Add flour mixture; beat.
Stir in nuts.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: so rice pudding
directions: Prepare rice.
Heat oven to 350°; grease an 8-inch pan. Combine next ingredients except raisins.
Pour egg mixture over rice; add raisins.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: ham sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water and cook until thick.
May add 1/2 cup cider and 1/4 cup Amaretto.
Use over ham or as a side dish for ham.

title: apple halushki
directions: In bowl, mix milk, beaten eggs, salt and sugar.
Stir in flour gradually.
When batter is ready, drop it from a spoon in boiling water.
See that the spoon includes a bit of apple each time. Test the Apple Halushki by cutting one in half for doneness.
If the inside is cooked through then it is done.
Serve with melted butter.
Enjoy!

title: sugar cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Knead slightly.
Flatten 1 tablespoon dough with sugared cup bottom.
Bake at 350° about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: herbed sausage links and apples
directions: Slice peeled and cored apples into rings.
Heat butter in skillet.
Add apples and cook until fruit just softens.
Remove from pan.
Add sausage to same pan and fry it until browned.
Pour off fat.
Add herbs and cider to pan and bring to gentle boil. Continue to cook until the sausage is thoroughly cooked and the liquid is reduced to a thick syrup.
Return apples to pan to reheat them and serve.
Serves four.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve hot or cold.

title: sliced potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a wooden spoon to prevent knife from cutting through.
Insert onion slices into potato slices, at least 5 to 6 per potato.
Drizzle butter over potatoes and sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper.
In microwave-safe dish, cook on High power 15 minutes.
Rotate dish once halfway through cooking cycle. Serves 4.

title: layered salad
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch serving dish with pieces of lettuce. Over this,
sprinkle
the
green
pepper, red pepper, celery, onion and
peas.
Mix
mayonnaise,
sour
cream and sugar and spread over the peas.
Sprinkle the top with the grated cheese and bacon bits.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients; cover and let set for 48 hours for full flavor.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat ingredients (except apples), liquids first.
Grease tube pan and flour it.
Put 1/2 batter in pan.
Slice 1/2 of the apples on top of batter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Add other half of batter.
Add more apples on top and cinnamon and sugar. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and simmer 15 minutes.

title: hoagie sandwich
directions: Chop onion.
Make hamburger balls, mixing in onion.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Cook in 400° oven until done. Heat sauce.
Toast rolls.
Put hamburger on roll and cover with sauce.
Add cheese.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Chop onion, cucumber and tomatoes into tiny pieces.
Cook spaghetti until done.
Rinse in cold water.
Add to onion, cucumber and tomatoes.
Add Italian dressing; mix well.
Add McCormick seasoning to taste.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: dutch salad
directions: Run ingredients through a food chopper.
Cook until soft in water to cover, with 1 cup salt.
Drain and rinse in cold water.

title: no roll pastry
directions: Cream together and press into pie plate.
Bake in oven about 20 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole combine beans, 1/2 can French fried onion, soup, milk and pepper.
Bake 40 minutes.
Top with remaining onion.
Bake an additional 5 minutes. Serves 6.

title: hot salsa
directions: Combine tomatoes, chili peppers, jalapenos, onion, coriander and cilantro in blender.
After blended, stir in lime juice, salt and pepper to taste.
(Reduce jalapenos for milder taste, add more if you dare.)

title: terry's tart lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until firm.
Top with meringue and chill.

title: cajun jambalaya(rice cooker recipe)
directions: Chop onion, then smother in oil.
Add chopped up sausage and salt and pepper, then add parsley and tomato sauce.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Put rice in cooker, then add butter and tomato sauce mixture.
Stir in shrimp.
It's done when rice cooker bell rings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: For crust, unroll crescent rolls and gently pat into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch ungreased baking pan.
Bake according to package directions. Cool on wire rack.
Meanwhile, stir together the cream cheese, dressing and dill weed.
Spread cream cheese mixture evenly over the crust.
Sprinkle with desired vegetable toppings and the shredded cheese.
Gently press vegetables and cheese into the cream cheese mixture.
Chill about 1 hour before serving.

title: chocolate glaze topping
directions: Melt chocolate and butter or margarine over low heat.
Remove from heat; stir in confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Mix in hot water, one tablespoon at a time.

title: dump cake
directions: Empty pie filling into a 9 x 13-inch pan and spread around (does not have to be perfect, just not in a mound).
Empty pineapple the same way.
Dump dry cake mix on top of filling and pineapple.
Just spread so it's not mounded.
Slice stick of butter and scatter slices on top.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Let cool and serve with pie server.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla. Beat in eggs.
Blend in chocolate.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Bake in greased 10 x 15-inch pan for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut while hot. Remove from pan immediately.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: spicy barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and drain. Add rest of ingredients. Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: crandyberry salad
directions: Combine jello and water; refrigerate until firm.

title: chicken swiss
directions: Make a mix with flour, salt and butter.
Add milk slowly, bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Add chicken stock and wine. Place chicken breasts in baking dish and top each with 1 slice of cheese.
Pour sauce over meat.
Top with crushed onion and garlic croutons and drizzle melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Season to taste.

title: pear salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Put in blender, then add cream cheese.
Drain pears, reserve juice to make 1 cup.
Add water to make 1 cup complete, put in blender along with pears. Blend on high until smooth.
Add Cool Whip with blended liquid, again blend on high until all is smooth.
Pour in glass bowl and refrigerate until mold is set or overnight.

title: ann's broccoli salad
directions: Cut flowerets off broccoli.
Peel stalk of broccoli.
Slice stalk.
Add sunflower seeds, raisins and onion to broccoli.
Mix Miracle Whip, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over broccoli
mix.
Add bacon and mix well.

title: lime pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup cold water and cornstarch to a paste. Mix hot water and sugar in saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Combine this mixture with the cornstarch paste and cook until mixture begins to thicken, about 15 minutes.

title: stir-fry
directions: Wash Boston butts good.
Season to taste (salt, pepper, Accent and garlic powder).
(Any kind of meat can be substituted; chicken or beef.)
Fry in oil until brown on both sides.
Remove from pan. Cut meat off bone into strips.
Pour out any remaining oil from frying pan.
Return strips to frying pan.
Pour teriyaki over meat; stir.
Place top on frying pan over medium heat; stir occasionally.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes or until meat feels tender when poked with a fork.
Turn heat off and serve over hot rice or potatoes.
Cook rice according to cooking instructions. (Any vegetables you like can be added to stir-fry.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar and Rice Krispies.

title: scallop potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into shallow greased casserole dish. Dot the top with several pats of butter. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: easy dessert
directions: Mix jello, 1 tablespoon sugar added with only 2 1/2 cups boiling water; set aside.
Break up 1/2 angel food cake into pieces.
Place in bottom of angel food cake pan evenly.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chocolate chips with 14 ounces almond bark in a large saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat. Stir in marshmallows, cereal and nuts.
Pour into greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Melt remaining 2 ounces of almond bark and oil over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Drizzle over pizza.
Refrigerate until firm.
May keep out at room temperature.

title: jane's lime-pear jello salad
directions: Heat
1 cup pear juice.
Add Jell-O and dissolve.
Mash pears and
combine with cream cheese.
Add Jell-O.
Let stand in refrigerator
until
almost set.
Add 2 cups Cool Whip and stir together.
Chill 4 hours.

title: frittatensuppe(clear soup with sliced unsweetened pancakes.)
directions: Put the bones into a pot and fill it up with water so that the bones are covered.
Add celery, turnip, carrots, leek and root of parsley.
Peel the onions, cut them into two parts and lay them on the hot oven until they become light brown (you don't have to use a pan!).
Add onions to the soup.
Heat it up until the water is boiling and then simmer it on lower temperature.
Add the rest of herbs and spices and season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: lime jello mold
directions: Cook Jell-O according to package directions.
Let it cool.
Add pint of sour cream slowly to cooling Jell-O.
Take eggbeater and blend ingredients.
Add crushed pineapple.
Stir into mixture and let it cool.
Place into mold.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: congo bars
directions: Beat margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add flour and baking soda, then chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: rust remover
directions: Mix together in small bowl.
Take dry cloth; rub rusted area. Rust instantly depletes from your metal and brass treasures.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Pretty tasty!

title: tropical salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water. Chill until slightly thickened. Combine all other ingredients and add to Jell-O.
Chill.
Unmold and garnish with greens and whole walnuts.

title: grandma's corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix the flour, corn meal, sugar, salt and baking soda in a medium bowl. Mix vinegar, milk, beaten egg and melted butter in a small bowl (vinegar and milk will sour).
Mix liquid ingredients into dry ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dad's door county chili
directions: Saut ground beef. Add remaining ingredients. Cook slowly 2 hours or longer.

title: spinach dip
directions: Defrost and drain spinach.
In food processor, chop onion, water chestnuts and spinach, then add vegetable soup mix.
In large bowl, mix chopped ingredients, mayonnaise, sour cream and lemon juice.
Be sure to mix well and let set in refrigerator. Get a loaf of pumpernickel bread, cut off the top portion and hollow out the inside.
Put dip inside and serve.
This is also good on a baked potato.

title: artichoke cannelloni with lemon bechamel sauce(makes 6 servings)
directions: Drain artichoke hearts thoroughly; dice and set aside.
Cook pasta in a large pot of boiling salted water until al dente.

title: microwave popcorn
directions: Put popcorn in microwave for 3 1/2 minutes.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add juice from pineapple. Add cottage cheese, evaporated milk, pineapple and walnuts.
Put in refrigerator.
When set or before serving, garnish with grapes, sliced in half.

title: curried cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt the butter or margarine and saute the onion and garlic for a few minutes.
Add the curry, pepper, broth and water to the pan and bring the soup to a boil.
Add the broccoli and potato.
When the mixture returns to a boil, reduce the heat, cover the pan and simmer the soup for about 20 minutes or until the vegetables are tender.
Puree the soup in batches in a blender or food processor.
Return the puree to the pan, stir in the milk and cook the soup over low heat until it is hot (but do not boil it).

title: plum nut pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together cheese, cream cheese and mashed garlic or chopped onion.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: fudge bonbons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a medium saucepan, combine chocolate chips and butter or margarine.
Cook and stir over very low heat until chips are melted and smooth.
Add milk; mix well.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, nuts, chocolate mixture and vanilla; mix well.
Shape 1 tablespoonful, using measuring spoon, of dough around candy kisses.
Place 1 inch apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cookies will be soft and appear shiny, but will become firm as they cool.
Do not overbake. Remove from cookie sheets; cool and drizzle with icing.

title: williamsburg soup
directions: Chop vegetables.
Cook in small amount of water for 20 minutes. Melt butter and blend in flour thoroughly.
Heat broth, cream and add very gradually to butter and flour mixture.
Stir until all lumps disappear.
Add vegetables (water and all).
Stir and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Season to taste.
Add meat and rice. Cook over low heat until meat is heated.
Makes 12 servings.

title: thick hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat in melting butter.
Add sugar and cream and stir until well blended.
Put over medium heat, stirring constantly, until all sugar is dissolved.
Do not let come to a hard boil, but cook slowly 4 minutes.
Beat in vanilla.

title: pepper steak
directions: Serve with rice.
Cut beef into 1/4-inch strips (partially frozen beef, slices easier).
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add beef and cook about 5 minutes, turning frequently, or until brown.
Stir in water, onion, garlic salt and ginger.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 12 to 15 minutes.
Add green pepper last 5 minutes of simmering.
While beef simmers, cook rice as directed on package.

title: peach cream pie
directions: Do not whip the cream.
Mix all ingredients well.
Add cinnamon.
Pour into deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot spiced wassail
directions: Put spices in cheesecloth bag.
Simmer all ingredients except orange slices, covered, for 10 minutes.
Remove spices.
Float orange slices.
You may also add 3 oranges, shredded, with cloves.

title: spinach swiss cheese quiche
directions: Toss cheese and flour together.
Combine milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Add spinach and cheese mixture to milk.
Mix well.
Pour into crust.
Top with dash of nutmeg.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mississippi corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, corn and sour cream. Pour in greased baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown ground beef, then drain. Mix all together; let simmer. Serve with shredded cheese and sour cream.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs; blend well.
Add oil, flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add soured milk (milk plus vinegar), cocoa, spices and nuts. Add zucchini.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam. Sprinkle chocolate chips over top and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: herman hot rolls
directions: Mix flour, Herman, baking powder, salt and oil.
Transfer to floured board.
Knead (needs very little handling).
Roll into balls or shape as desired.
Bake rolls on greased cookie sheet in 425° oven or 13 to 15 minutes or until browned.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Combine sliced strawberries and glaze; set aside.
Cream together the powdered sugar and cream cheese. Add evaporated milk and blend well.
Fold in Cool Whip. Break angel food cake into small chunks in a large bowl.
Combine with creamed mixture. Spread into long 13 x 9-inch dish or larger.
Spread strawberry mixture on top. Cover and chill.
Keeps well for several days.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, zucchini and nuts.
Pour batter into cupcake liners.
Bake at 350°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: In a large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar; add the eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add almond extract; stir in flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Add mixture.
Spoon the pie filling into the pan in 16 spots, spacing 4 spoonfuls evenly in each direction.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until golden brown (batter will rise to the top).
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve.

title: the dish
directions: Saute ground beef.
Cut up onions and green pepper and put in pan with a little water and steam.
Drain off water.
Place all ingredients in a large pot except noodles and enough cheese to put on top of casserole.
Cook on low heat, stirring frequently, until the cheese is melted.
Cook noodles and add to sauce.
Place in casserole and top with remaining cheese.
Cook about 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 6.
Casserole may be frozen, but do not cook in oven until ready to serve.

title: buenos nachos
directions: Combine cream cheese, guacamole and sour cream, mixing until well blended.
Spread cream cheese mixture onto serving platter; top with chips.

title: fruit squares
directions: In a large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar.
Add the eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Spoon pie filling into the cake in 16 spots, spacing 4 spoonfuls evenly in each direction and bake.
Flip cake on serving plate.
Dust with powdered sugar if desired.
This is great served warm.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine sour cream and 1/2 of Ranch dressing mix package. Then add chicken, 1 cup of shredded cheese and olives. Spoon mixture down middle of tortillas and roll up. Place seam down in 9 x 13 baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup of cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: ground beef skillet supper
directions: Brown beef, leaving meat in chunky pieces.
Stir in onion soup and water, salt, carrots and noodles.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Uncover and cook about 10 minutes longer.

title: yams in orange cups
directions: Mash in mixer all ingredients.
Use enough water or juice from canned yams to make custard consistency.
Place in orange halves (orange removed with edges fluted).
Dot with butter.
Place in shallow pan to which 1/8-inch water has been added.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with slice of bacon.
Line slightly greased baking dish with chipped beef.
Place chicken over beef. Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken and refrigerate. When ready to serve, bake, uncovered, at 275° approximately 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Also makes good gravy to serve over rice.

title: salad dressing spice cake
directions: Sift
and
mix dry ingredients.
Add moist ingredients. Bake in lightly greased pan at 350° until done.

title: banana pudding
directions: Blend 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Add milk and cook over double boiler until thick, stirring constantly (approximately 15 minutes).
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add custard gradually to eggs.
Return to double boiler.
Cook two minutes.
Layer dish with wafers and bananas; cover with custard.

title: vegetable enchiladas
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 20 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Store in Tupperware at least 2 days.
Stir or shake daily and it will repickle with sweet flavor instead of salty.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cook sugar and Karo to rolling boil; remove for fire and add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add cereal and drop on oiled paper.

title: butter cookies for all seasons
directions: Cream butter in a large mixer bowl.
Gradually add sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, milk and vanilla.
In another bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually combine dry ingredients to butter mixture; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate about 1 hour or until thoroughly chilled.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: your own salsa
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Spread onto dinner plate.
In a bowl, add salsa and chopped vegetables.
Mix together.
Pour salsa mix on top of cream cheese.
Top with shredded cheese.
Place chips around outside of plate.
Serve.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Mix first 6 ingredients.
Bake with or without ready-to-use pie crust.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: refried beans with cheese
directions: Soak beans overnight, then bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 hours.
Do not drain.
Heat oil in skillet.
Cook onion and garlic.
Add chili powder, salt and tomato sauce; mix.
Remove beans from liquid.
Mash beans and add with liquid to skillet. Add cheese.
Serves 8.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese, juice and sugar.
Pour into crust. Layer bananas and pineapple, then Cool Whip.
Top with strawberries.
Chill 1 hour.

title: lazy cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Melt 1/2 cup butter in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Pour in batter.
Spread 1 can of your favorite fruit pie filling on the batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind together the cranberries, orange and sugar.
Let stand 1 hour.
Dissolve jello in water.
Mix these ingredients with celery, pineapple and nuts.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together.
Press in an ungreased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over crust.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over the top.
Allow to cool and cut into 12 bars.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with wafers.

Pat on bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan. Beat eggs, remaining butter and sugar for 15 minutes. Spread over crust. Slice bananas in 1/2-inch lengthwise portions and place in mixture. Spread pineapple over bananas, then cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with nuts, drizzle syrup over top and top with cherries.
Refrigerate. Serve cool.

title: swedish pickled beets
directions: Combine ingredients, bring to a boil; cool slightly.
Place beets in a deep bowl and pour dressing over beets.
Let stand for several hours in refrigerator or overnight.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain off fat. Stir in tomato sauce, garlic powder, mushrooms, salt and green beans.
Add any amount of the spices, if desired.
Simmer on stove.
Spread crescent rolls in pie pan.
Mix together Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Add egg.
Spread half of cheese mixture on crust.
Press meat mixture over cheese.
Top with remaining cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° until crust is brown.
If made ahead of time, crust will be soggy.

title: raspberry dessert(serves 9)
directions: Combine condensed milk and lemon juice.
Fold in whipped cream, raspberry jam and nuts.
Put a layer of graham cracker crumbs on bottom of oblong Pyrex dish (12 x 7 1/2-inch size).

title: lo-cal tuna salad
directions: Boil macaroni in salted water until tender.
Drain and rinse with cold water; drain well.
Chill.
Mix cottage cheese, salad dressing and lemon juice.
Pour over macaroni, tuna, celery, pickles and egg.
Toss enough to mix well. Serve on lettuce. Sprinkle with savor salt for color and added flavor.
Serves 4.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening, flour, sugar and salt into the size of peas. Beat egg; add water and vinegar.
Gradually add flour mixture. Mix until you can handle. This will keep a week or more in a lightly covered container in the refrigerator.

title: gold rush brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Put into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: creamy italian dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender, cover, blend on medium 15 seconds or until smooth.
Chill.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: About 45 minutes before serving:
On a cutting board, trim fat from tenderloin.
Cut meat across the grain into 1/2-inch slices. Cut each slice into 1/2-inch cubes.
Dry strips well on paper towels.

In a 10-inch skillet over high heat, in 1 tablespoon hot butter or margarine (be careful not to let it burn), cook half of meat, stirring constantly, until lightly browned or about 1 minute (meat will be rare).
Pour meat and drippings into a medium bowl and set aside.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown
onion
in butter.
Add ground beef and brown and season.
Cut cabbage into squares. Add to beef mixture.
Cover and cook
slowly until the cabbage becomes translucent (about 10 minutes).
Add cheese, sour cream and wine.
Mix thoroughly.
Put in
quart greased casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with crushed cheese crackers.
Put in greased casserole.
Bake at 375° until bubbly (25 to 30 minutes) and browned.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: After cooking the chicken, pull out the bones and cut into bite size pieces.
Place in baking dish, adding the pineapple. Saute diced celery in margarine; add chicken.

title: peanut butter creme pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, peanut butter and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell.
Garnish as desired (i.e. drizzle Hershey's syrup, shave chocolate, etc.).
Freeze.
Thaw 20 minutes before serving.

title: baked whitefish basque style
directions: Coat the bottom of ovenproof casserole with half the oil and place fillets of whitefish in dish.
Heat rest of oil in large skillet and saute onion, pepper, garlic, tomatoes and bay leaf. Add salt and pepper and white wine.
Allow mixture to boil; then pour over fish and bake, uncovered, in preheated 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily.

title: asparagus and tomato slices
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut stem ends off tomatoes and slice each into 3 thick slices. Cut asparagus spears in half and arrange on top of tomato slices in a buttered, shallow baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients and spoon over asparagus. Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted. Do not overbake. Serves 6 to 8.

title: creamed skallops casserole
directions: Mix.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple icebox pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks. Fold in sugar and 1/2 cup pineapple juice. Cook until thick; remove from heat. Add jello. After it dissolves, add butter and pineapple and remaining juice. Pour over vanilla wafers. Add nuts and stiffly beaten egg whites. Keep in the refrigerator.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Combine and add flour and salt.
Chill dough 3 to 4 hours before rolling.
Use a little extra flour on work surface and rolling pin when rolling dough. Form shapes with cookie cutters or roll into small balls.
Lift out the dough scraps between the shapes and re-roll them. Bake on greased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes or until slightly colored.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix butter, flour and nuts together and press into 8 x 10-inch pan or square casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix together.
Chill several hours before serving.
(Can use blueberry pie filling.)

title: granny mac's nut cake
directions: Mix the
fruit
and
nuts
with
1 cup of flour and set aside. Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one or two at a time, and beat
well.
Add
flour and beat.
Stir in vanilla, then mix
in fruit
and
nuts.
Bake in tube pan (greased and floured) for about 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: edible play dough
directions: Mix peanut butter and dry milk.
Add honey, if desired.
Knead and mix until dough-like.
Model and eat.
Offer raisins, banana chips, etc. for decoration.

title: oven meat balls
directions: Combine and mix ground beef, salt, onion, oatmeal, pepper and milk.
Form into small balls.
Place in baking dish.
Set aside. Mix together catsup, vinegar, sugar and water.
Pour over meat balls.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Serve over potatoes, noodles, rice, etc.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix eggs and granulated sugar.
Add vinegar and salt; boil until thick.
Add salad dressing and mayonnaise.
Add evaporated milk.
Mix well and pour over potatoes or macaroni, cooked.

title: shiny carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling, salted water until tender; drain. Melt butter in frying pan; stir in sugar.
Add carrots.
Cook over moderate heat, turning several times until well glazed.
Garnish with parsley.

title: curry vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve as dip with vegetable tray.

title: lamb kabobs (greek)
directions: Mix wine, lemon juice, olive oil, salt, pepper, garlic and oregano to make marinade.
Place meat and sliced onions in bowl; pour marinade over.
Refrigerate overnight or 6 to 8 hours, turning once or twice.

title: chews
directions: Mix all ingredients together with electric mixer and add nuts last.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch or larger pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
(Check after 25 minutes as oven heat may vary.)

title: jello vanilla pudding pecan pie
directions: Blend pudding with corn syrup.
Gradually add evaporated milk and egg, stirring to blend.
Then add pecans.
Pour over pie shell. Bake at 375° until top is firm and begins to crack, approximately 40 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels in saucepan over low heat with 1 1/2 sticks of butter and evaporated milk.
Make cake according to box directions. Pour 1/2 of cake batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Pour caramel sauce over partially baked cake and add chocolate chips and pecan pieces. Pour remaining cake batter over top.
Bake for 20 more minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Don't cut while hot.

title: baked chicken and macaroni
directions: Combine milk and soup.
Add rest of ingredients except parsley, pimento and 1 egg.
Refrigerate overnight, tightly covered.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with peaches and liquid. Sprinkle sugar over peaches, then the cake mix.
Melt margarine and pour over cake mix, being sure to moisten all of the mix. Bake for approximately 45 minutes at 350° or until it browns and looks done.

title: new york cream cheese cake
directions: Cream Ricotta cheese and cream cheese together.
Add sugar and eggs, one at a time, until all are well beaten in.
Add flour, sour cream and vanilla.
Pour in greased spring-pan (10-inch).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Turn oven off and leave cheese cake in the oven for 1 more hour.
Do not open oven door during these 2 hours!
Sprinkle top with cinnamon before putting in oven or wait until it is all done and add favorite fruit.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix and pour into greased muffin pans.
(Stir in blueberries last.)
Bake at 350° until done.

title: low calorie pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease or spray a 9-inch pie pan. Put all ingredients in blender, food processor or mixing bowl. Blend one minute or beat 2 minutes with mixer.
Pour into pie pan and bake for 50 minutes or until center is puffed up.
Makes its own crust.

title: butter pecan turtles
directions: Combine and mix at low speed until fine.
Press into baking pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup of pecans evenly over crust.

title: marilyn's chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and bake at 350 degrees until toothpick comes out clean.
Do not overbake.
Prepare frosting by melting butter over low heat.
Add marshmallow and stir until melted.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients until blended and smooth.
Cover and refrigerated 30 minutes or until cold and very firm.
Beat with mixer on high speed 3 minutes or until smooth and creamy.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix as for any cake.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Drain broccoli and put in buttered baking dish once it has been cooked.
Put bread cubes on top of broccoli.
In double boiler melt cheese.
Mix soup with cheese.
Pour over broccoli mixture and bake at 350 degrees until bubbly, usually 30 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, margarine and pecans; press in bottom of sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole #2
directions: Break broccoli in bite size pieces.
In a double boiler or in the microwave, melt butter and cheese.
Add lightly beaten eggs, cottage cheese and flour.
Add broccoli.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot sandwiches
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion, chilies and cheese.
Simmer until blended.
Serve on rye, French or what kind of bread you have.

title: italian chicken
directions: You will also need 1 large Reynolds oven cooking bag.

title: glazed meatballs
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, onions, milk, egg, parsley, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper; mix well. Shape into 1-inch meatballs. Cook in hot oil over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until browned. Drain on paper towels.

title: microwave stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: In a large saucepan on the stove, bring 6 cups of water and 1 teaspoon of salt to boiling.
Add cabbage leaves and simmer about 2 or 3 minutes or just long enough to make leaves pliable.
Drain leaves on paper towels.
Put beef into a 1 1/2-quart glass baking dish.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook in microwave oven 4 minutes at High or until meat is no longer pink.
Stir occasionally.
Add rice, onion, egg and poultry seasoning to beef and mix.
Divide meat mixture into 8 even portions.
Cut the core out of the cabbage leaf.
Place one portion of meat in center of each cabbage leaf.
Fold 2 sides of leaf over meat and roll up leaves from the end.
Arrange cabbage rolls, seam side down, in a 2-quart glass baking dish.
Combine tomato sauce, brown sugar, lemon juice and water in a small bowl.
Pour over cabbage rolls.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook in microwave oven 10 minutes at High or until heated.
Rearrange once during the cooking period. Remove from oven.
Cover with plastic wrap and allow to stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Blend margarine, flour and garlic until pasty.
Add half and half and both cheeses.
Simmer over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
In a small pan, boil shrimp in own juices until cooked through.
Drain and add shrimp to mixture.
Stir well and pour over noodles.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook all together a few minutes and pour over meat with foil under it in an iron skillet. After meat browns, cover with foil and cook until meat is tender.

title: snooky's baked squash casserole
directions: Drain water from one can of squash.
Add one well beaten egg, diced onion, melted butter and stuffing mix.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Put in casserole and bake in moderate oven, 325°, until light brown and firm, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: jefferson davis pie
directions: Beat all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°,
then at 350°
until firm.

title: apricot bars
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients until crumbly (crust).
Press into slightly greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 12 minutes.

title: beef pie
directions: Brown meat with onion and salt and pepper.
Drain fat and stir in soup and beans.
Cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
Peel, then cut into bite size pieces.
Mix eggs, pimento, sweet pickle relish, salad dressing and potatoes together.
Add sugar, salt and pepper to taste.

title: impossible broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Use a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Rinse broccoli to thaw and drain.
Mix broccoli, 2 cups of cheese and onion in plate.
Grease pie plate first.
Beat milk, eggs, baking mix, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted comes out clean, 25 to 35 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and put back in oven 1 or 2 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: spanish rice
directions: Rinse rice with cold water until water is clear; drain well, then let set until rice is completely dry.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add rice and spread evenly.
When rice is brown, sprinkle garlic salt over it.
Add tomato sauce, bell pepper, onion and just enough boiling water to cover rice (approximately 1-inch).
Cover and let simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove cover and stir.
Replace lid and continue cooking for another 10 minutes. Serves 6.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil. Add all the other ingredients and cook until chicken and vegetables are done, about 40 minutes.

title: glorified gingerbread
directions: Grease	and
flour
pans.
Mix	sugar, flour and spices together.
Then
cut
in shortening with pastry blender or two knives.
Save
1/3	cup
of
mixture for on top.
Make hole in remaining
mixture.
Add egg and molasses, sour milk, soda and salt.
Mix	together
and pour into 2 (9-inch) pans.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans; chill. Roll into ball. Roll in chopped pecans.

title: lazy cabbage roll
directions: Mix and bake in 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creamy fruit mold
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and gelatin. Add water. Stir until gelatin is dissolved. Refrigerate until thickened, about 1 hour, stirring frequently. Add mayonnaise. Whisk until smooth. Stir in fruit and pecans. Pour into a 1-quart mold that has been coated with nonstick cooking spray. Chill until firm. Unmold onto a serving platter. Yield: 6 servings.

title: hot mustard sauce
